  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

>Subject: Re: Power Imagine
>From:    Mike Halvorson
>Date:    22/11/95  6:02 pm
>
>Gary
>
>I hate to tell people they are wrong, but the Amiga version IS compiled for
the
>040 CPU, I have no idea why you think differently, if you are just repeating
>what some idiot said from something you read, I am sorry, but we were ahead
of
>eveyone on this arena.  We has the first 040 code, long before Newtek or
anyone
>else.
>
>So if you want to send more money for what we have done, make it a big check
>something like 200K or so, I can take a vacation and I will send you a new
>version of the software eveyday for a year.
>
>Ok back to reality
>
>Mike

How many people are running the fp version on an 020 or 030, raise your
hands.

BTW. Fully blown optimized 040 code will not run on an 020 or 030. 
     Do the math.


