@node IML-76 " MSG-76  Subject: Re: Sorry..and an idea.....:)
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Sorry..and an idea.....:)
Date:    Wednesday, 06 December 1995 12:33:00 
From:    Steven M Powell <afn27231@afn.org>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

For Imagine I highly recomend the Firecraker 24 from Impulse. Imagine 
will render directly to it. Its output is great and it is easy to transfer 
to video. I have a "true color" card for my PC, but the FC24 looks better 
everytime. I have seen them selling for $125.00 at some dealers. Most 
Amiga software supports it also. It is a display card only, so no 
workbench emulation. the resolution is 368, 512, 768, 1024 by 240, 480.
I really like mine, and as long as I have an Amiga , I will never sell it.

  Render On.....                             Phoenix
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

 e-mail: afn27231@afn.org                 Steven M Powell
                                          Gainesville FL

 Homepage: http://www.afn.org/~afn27231

