@node IML-112 " MSG-112  Subject: Re: Re[2]: Power Imagine
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Re[2]: Power Imagine
Date:    Thursday, 07 December 1995 13:09:18 
From:    David Alan Steiger <das@barnard.csustan.edu>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

On Sat, 25 Nov 1995, Michael Rivers wrote:
> >From:    Mike Halvorson
> >
> >I hate to tell people they are wrong, but the Amiga version IS compiled for
> the 040 CPU,

Mr. Halvorson:

It may indeed be compiled for a '40 to run.
It is NOT compiled SPECIFICALLY for a '40 to run OPTIMALLY.
This is the point.

Back when you allowed the editors to be loaded singly, I had to TURN OFF my
'40 "copyback" mode. Otherwise when switching editors the program would 
crash, like any other program thats WASN'T '40 aware.

I hate SHOWING people they are wrong but...

Dave

