Nancy, I just tried to do exactly what you wanted, and here's
how I did it...
Apply the brush with default values.  Then, Edit Axes.  Rotate the y
axis 90 degrees.  Then re-size everything so that it fits over your
terrain.  You can check how it will look if you click on "from object"
for preview size.  The top rightmost quadrant of the bounding box has
to completely fit over your object.
(I just mapped my face onto a montain range...scary stuff!)
Hope you're using 4.0!
