@node IML-209 " MSG-209  Subject: Rendering times and IOR.
@toc contents

Subject: Rendering times and IOR.
Date:    Saturday, 09 December 1995 13:38:49 
From:    Chris Hall <chris.hall@dial.pipex.com>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

I've noticed recently whilst rendering glass that if you set the IOR to 1 it
takes quite a lot longer to render in trace mode than if the IOR is set
above 1. Why is this so? Surely it's easier to render glass with an IOR of 1
because there is no bending effect and you should see exactly the same as
you'd see without the glass. For a quick demo go into the attributes
requester, set the filter right up, turn on backgrounds and watch as it
displays the preview. Now set the IOR to something other than 1 and watch
the speed difference. If this doesn't work for you what am I doing wrong!!

Thanks for reading all this.
Chris Hall.

