Subject: VS: Problems with Imagine 4
Date:    Saturday, 09 December 1995 21:31:41 
From:    Barry Winter <bwinter@inet.uni-c.dk>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


>I have recently upgraded my Amiga version of Imagine from 3.0 to 4.0.
One of the main benefits I was hoping for was the different screen
resolutions (mainly 800x600) available. I have a 4000/030 so I have =
turned
on the AA chipset option in preferences and set SMOD to 1 (800 pixels =
wide).
No joy. All I get is the same old 640x480 all the time.

For the Amiga version Richard you'll need a Retina compatible display =
card to display the higher resolution but with the AA chipset you'll be =
able to access the 256 colour display. That's one of the reasons that I =
must confess to going over to the pc version after using Imagine from =
version 2 on the Amiga, the easy acces to higher resolutions and the =
speed of operation using 256 colour mode.

>The other question I have is how do I stop the sky banding that occurs =
in
renders with colours set in the Action Editor Globals.
I seem to remember a sky blending setting but I can't find it now.

Isn't the blending now set permanently to 255?

best wishes Barry







