@node IML-224 " MSG-224  Subject: Advertisements
@toc contents

Subject: Advertisements
Date:    Sunday, 10 December 1995 09:33:18 
From:    helmy@voyager.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

I understand that some may object to our offer of "3D OBJECT/INTERNET
SUBSCRIPTION", but we have also had a number of people who are
interested enough to subscribe to our services.  We are asking for a
reasonable fee because we have employees who have to get their salaries
every month.  I also understand that this is not the best place to
"advertise" your service, but when it is specifically targeting Imagine
users then I couldn't think of a better place to advertise this service,
because 1. Its very affordable (approximately $1.00 per object)    2. It
is Imagine specific (which makes it unique)  3. This would benefit any
Imagine user who doesn't like to model or achieve special effects such
as (smoke or fire), and likes spend time animating or rendering scenes.

I respect anyone's criticism towards our offer, but I dont think that it
would be fair for us to not let Imagine users know about this offer.  We
all know that not much happens (as far as services, books, or
third-party development goes) in the Imagine arena, so we thought that
this could be a cool way to send users cool objects and to have them
create even more stunning images.  Thank you.

                           -------------------------
                             H"E"L"M"Y PRODUCTIONS
