@toc contents

Subject: Hiding your head in the sand
Date:    Sunday, 10 December 1995 13:47:38 
From:    Mike McCool <mikemcoo@efn.org>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

> 
> I know this is still off topic, but not even congress can screw up the
> internet.  They do not have jursidiction over the whole world.  And there are
> encryption methods which even the NSA can't crack.  It's allot of polictical
> hot air and nothing to get to worried about.

Not trying to start a fight, nor let this tangent distract too much from 
the main priority of my machine and this list, which is to render a more 
beautiful universe,--but hey, this is only the first step. 

Whenever a winger, left or right, starts dragging morality into the 
issue, you can bet he/she's smokescreening.  What we're really talking about 
here is the old bottom line, THE BUCK.  

The moguls of the communications industry feel a lot of the above
slipping through their fingers in the net.  And since most of them are of
the ultra-conservative ilk that isn't satisfied with some, but wants it
ALL, they're using all their power to close the cracks and seal the leaks. 

This bit of legislation will set the precedent.  For their goal 
is clearly to control everyone's access to the internet.  

The cynic in me would go so far as to contend that most of these moralizers 
wouldn't care if their own children could access pictures of the virgin 
mary being mounted by a donkey, so long as they got their piece of the 
action.  

