@node IML-239 " MSG-239  Subject: Virtual Memory
@toc contents

Subject: Virtual Memory
Date:    Sunday, 10 December 1995 20:25:24 
From:    Philip Marley <pjm100@unix.york.ac.uk>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

      Can anyone help me out with a few problems I'm having 
virtual-memory wise?

      My system is an A1200 with a Viper '030 board with 4MB RAM. I'm 
trying to use VMM to give me some virtual RAM so I can renders 
some complex objects. I've de-fragmented my hard drive, set up a pagefile 
and so on and VMM seems to be fine, but when I do a quickrender on a 
complex object Imagine comes up with error 800000(lots of 0's)002 and 
freezes. 
      Flipping back to Workbench and watching the VMM status display 
revealed that this was happening when Imagine ran out of virtual ram 
(when I'd set VMM up to give me 5MB of the stuff). So I set up 7MB of 
virtual RAM, and now Imagine does the same act when it gets down to 2MB 
of virtual RAM, so it would seem that a lack of RAM isn't the problem. I 
should only need 11MB of RAM to render the stuff I'm rendering, and my 
current setup should give me 13 MB (6 real and 7 virtual). Any ideas? Is 
Imagine not using my Chip RAM, by any chance? I have an MMU (or at least 
I do according to my board's sales specs).

Anybody got any other tips about virtual RAM, (software to use, etc).

                                              Ta,
                                                Philip


