Subject: Re: ALERT - Protest Internet Censorship Bills, Tues 12/12/95
Date:    Sunday, 10 December 1995 22:45:26 
From:    sgiff@airmail.net (Stephen Gifford)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

>In a message dated 95-12-10 14:30:33 EST, you write:
>
>>What your congress seems to forget is that the Internet, like it or
>>not, is now an international network and many/most of us aren't even
>>governed by US law. The Web, their main source of angst, isn't even based
>>in the States. It was started/based at CERN in Europe. They can legislate
>>all they
>>like, but they'll have to cut every phone line and satellite link into and
