>>
>>Bill B
>
>Well said.  Our goverment is already involved in many issues it has no point
>being involved in and now they seem to suffer from dillusions of being able
>to affect the internet.  99% of them don't know what it is, and Clinton is
>just plain lost all the time.  There is no reason for anyone to be concerned
>about what the U.S. Goverment may attempt to do to the internet.  They simply
>cannot control it.
>
>Bob...........
>Imagine renderings.
>http://home.aol.com/robsampson
>
Not to get into a big argument over a topic unrelated to the list but since
it's important that people don't just shrug this off I feel I must reply.
The fact is that Congress can pass legislation that would make it illegal to
download or upload anything of a specific nature here in America.  Who cares
if you could still get porno or something they deem unsuitable from Europe.
If they pass legislation and make it Illegal, you could have FBI or some
other new burocracy monitoring what you download and you could go to jail
for a completely unconstitional issue.  What about the IRS?  If they start
to accuse you, it's up to you to prove your own innocence.  In the meantime
they can freeze your assets and cause you all sorts of problems that are
completely unconsitutional yet they can do it!  Believe me if Congress
passes legislation to control the Internet, it will have a huge effect here
in the US, simply because companies that provide internet service will
become extremely paranoid about who they let subscribe and they will have to
severely monitor their own customers to make sure they don't put anything
illegal on there own servers.  Otherwise they will be busted as well.

There is a far bigger issue at stake here and that is the fact that
Government realizes that knowledge is Power and the internet is the best
means of the people communicating knowledge to each other.  You take away
their ability to do that or you give them the rights to start monitoring
peoples private transmissions and what do you have.  You have Romania, or a
dozen other Police States like we have scene in the past.

Please do not take the Internet Censorship Protest lightly.  Call your
congressman.

s.g.

Visit Me at the Magick Rainbow:
http://alpha1.iadfw.net/~sgiff/


