@node IML-244 " MSG-244  Subject: Re: Advertisements
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Advertisements
Date:    Sunday, 10 December 1995 23:18:38 
From:    sgiff@airmail.net (Stephen Gifford)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

>I understand that some may object to our offer of "3D OBJECT/INTERNET
>SUBSCRIPTION", but we have also had a number of people who are
>interested enough to subscribe to our services.  We are asking for a
>reasonable fee because we have employees who have to get their salaries
>every month.  I also understand that this is not the best place to
>"advertise" your service, but when it is specifically targeting Imagine
>users then I couldn't think of a better place to advertise this service,


In helmy's defense, I think we should be helping each other as much as
possible on this list.  However I can really agree with the person who
mentioned how the IML is one place we would like not to have to get direct
mail advertisments or junk mail every day.  I think it is reasonable to post
such an ad once every few months.  I certainly would be against seeing it
every week.  Especially if more than a few started doing it.  That I doubt
will ever happen.  Maybe Helmy should have to pay by giving everyone a free
