> 

Right.  This kind of gullibility must be as old as Man.  Take for 
example, the figure of Joseph.  

One day he decides he'll surprise Mary and come home for lunch.  Only he 
finds she's upstairs being shagged by the Holy Ghost.  She sounds so 
enraptured, he's shy to interrupt, so he sits in the doorway, head in 
hands. 

The White-winged Dove comes down and whispers in his ear not to worry. 
"Hey, don't you know we're gonna take care of you?  We're gonna fix it so
no one ever calls you a cuckold.  We're gonna patent this new thing 
called 'immaculate conception.' That way you won't ever look the fool." 

After a while, the Holy Ghost comes down, girding his loins and looking a
little weak in the knees.  He casts the White-winged Dove an inquiring 
glance. The Dove winks and flies off to heaven.  

The Holy Ghost begins to fade.  Muttering "If they buy this, they'll buy 
ANYTHING," He rubs his great hands together and begins making the mold 
for Richard Nixon. 


