@node IML-263 " MSG-263  Subject: Re: ALERT - Protest Internet Censorship Bills, Tues 12/12/95
@toc contents

Subject: Re: ALERT - Protest Internet Censorship Bills, Tues 12/12/95
Date:    Monday, 11 December 1995 05:57:11 
From:    RobSampson@aol.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

In a message dated 95-12-10 22:43:40 EST, you write:

>There is a far bigger issue at stake here and that is the fact that
>Government realizes that knowledge is Power and the internet is the best
>means of the people communicating knowledge to each other.  You take away
>their ability to do that or you give them the rights to start monitoring
>peoples private transmissions and what do you have.  You have Romania, or a
>dozen other Police States like we have scene in the past.
>
>Please do not take the Internet Censorship Protest lightly.  Call your
>congressman.


Stephen there has been via local bbs's a vast array of places in this country
for the free exchange of information and files for many years now.  Also for
many years now there have been numerous laws on the books making it illegal
to exchange copyrighted materials and/or certain types of pornography via
electronic means.  They do not work.  They never have worked.  At best they
have proved to be minor annoyances on occasion to some people who are blatant
about the exchange of these materials.  Generally the more attention the
subjects has gained amoungst those who utilize computers the more the laws
were broken.  The goverment stands no chance of policing the internet.  You
make a big jump from the censorship issue to the legalized monitoring of
communications occuring on the net.  That is not yet an issue.  But quite
frankly you would be naive to think that NSA does not already monitor
anything on the net that they want to.  They monitor most of the calls in
this country and communications around the world with mainframe machines
doing keyword searches.  Don't get me wrong.  I do not like the federal
goverment, irregardless of party.  It is to big and to much into our lives
already.  But there are many other more serious issues at stake in Washington
these days rather than worrying about something the goverment cannot
accomplish.

Bob................
