@toc contents

Subject: Re: Motion Blur
Date:    Monday, 11 December 1995 10:49:16 
From:    Vance Schowalter <viking@freenet.edmonton.ab.ca>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

Speaking of motion blur, I did a blur test which turned out really well. 
I have to find someone now who can upload the HAM and HAM8 versions to 
AmiNet for me.

The scene used the new starfield, space probe of my design, a planet, a 
molten planet. The camera was fixed, tracking the probe as it flies by. 
Simple test, but it looks pretty good.

Interesting note about the old starfield  and new starfield. When the new 
starfield has motion blur and your camera makes a quick motion like a 
pan, the stars stretch and fade out the faster the move goes, rather than 
stretching and staying bright. Slower movement retains bright, streaked 
stars. Looks interesting, anyhow. *8^)

Vance


