  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

  By definition, the .DXF format is ASCII. However, AutoCAD, which 
originated the .DXF format also has a .DWG format which is binary. Maybe 
this is what you are referring to? Can't be of much help for converters, 
the only way I know to convert is read the .DWG into AutoCAD and export 
as .DXF. I think I saw some articles about a few conversion packages that 
can read in .DWG but they are commercial.

