@node IML-285 " MSG-285  Subject: Tip: QuickEdges
@toc contents

Subject: Tip: QuickEdges
Date:    Monday, 11 December 1995 17:34:04 
From:    lund@hoa.ping.dk (Anders Lundholm)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


 Hey, A tip!

If you're modeling large complex models with 100's of 1000's of points then
why not use the 'quick edges' feature ?!. For instance, if you've got a
huge model of, let's say a pennywise, then try the following:

1. Mode/Pick Edges
2. Pick_Select/pick Range (1,100321,10) this will pick every 10. edge in
   the object.
3. Object/Make/Make Quick Edges.

4. Display/Newmode
5. Functions/QuickDraw All (select QuickEdges).


And wupti, there you are. A quickedges object, easy to view (you don't need
all points to know what's happening) and fast to display. I don't know for
sure, but using this method with a graphics card sure helps.

 o
/#\  Anders Lundholm . Alien Workshop (Tm) . Lund@Hoa.Ping.Dk
 ZZ Computer Graphics Design . 3D Modeling & Animation

