  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

> John Olson worte:

> Well guys, its been alot of fun, but after years of using Imagine I have
> come to a point where I have to leave it behind since I just got hired
> by a popular Game Company to do 3D graphics on the SGI platform.

Why get rid of a good thing.  I work for a company that develops on the SGI
platform.  I use my Amiga 2000 and Imagine to help develop graphics on the SGI
side.  If you know how to program, you could write a conversion program to take
all your Imagine objects with you to the SGI.  That's what I did.  At work we
don't have Alias|Wavefront so I can't speak on that, but for what we use at my
jobsite, Imagine is still a better modler.  I use Imagine to make most of the
objects that we use here.

If you can program, I suggest picking up the Imagine 3.0 Object File Format by
S. Kirvan.  The file can be found on Aminet in gfx/3d as "im3texdoc.lha".  You
may be able to to find it else were.  I got my copy off of GEnie.

Kevin -KV- Alvarado


