@node IML-300 " MSG-300  Subject: Re: Challenges
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Challenges
Date:    Monday, 11 December 1995 23:23:58 
From:    Dave Hardenbrook <DAVEH47@delphi.com>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

Mikael <mikael@pip.dknet.dk> askes:
>How do you create and animate a black hole?

Since black holes are really not "holes" at all, but collapsed stars from which
no light can escape, just use a primitive sphere that is totally black! :)

On the other hand, if you want something a little more dramatic, like a black
hole surrounded by an "accretion disk", I suggest putting your black sphere at 
the center of a disk or nearly flat cylinder and map a paint-program-produced 
multi-colored spiral to the disk.  Then to animate, just rotate the disk.

                             -- Dave

P.S. You might also try experimenting by applying fog various textures (e.g.
ghost, nebula, etc.) to the disk.
                             

                       @{"           Thread          293" link IML-293}
