@node IML-331 " MSG-331  Subject: Re: Virtual Memory
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Virtual Memory
Date:    Tuesday, 12 December 1995 16:58:53 
From:    rgreb@emmetpub.demon.co.uk (Rob Caunt)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

Philip Marley writes:
>     Can anyone help me out with a few problems I'm having 
>virtual-memory wise?
>
Hi Philip

Can't help you for certain, but it sounds as tho' your problem may be simply
lack of virtual memory. Perhaps your Amiga hasn't recognised the new 7MB
page size. Try installing from scratch. From what I hear, the best option
with VMM is to use a permanent disk partition, not a file, which is much
slower. You should go for a partition as large as you can afford the disk
space.

As for choice of software: VMM. Better than the commercial GigaMem anyway.
Neither are as good as the real thing (ie the silicon kind).

If you're still having problems "remember what you were doing and post the
IML".

-- 

"if you don't use the bins you can't come in."

Rob

