@node IML-332 " MSG-332  Subject: Realistic Earths
@toc contents

Subject: Realistic Earths
Date:    Tuesday, 12 December 1995 17:27:35 
From:    lund@hoa.ping.dk (Anders Lundholm)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

CC: Robsampson@aol.com

Letter from Anders Lundholm to Robsampson@aol.com Written 12 Dec 95 At 07:52:22
O'clock

Hi Robsampson@aol.com ...

 Rac> Hey hey hey:))))  Imagine is good but a photorealistic earth it cannot
 Rac> create:)

Yes!. Use a lot of CSG spheres with each having different fog-lenght
settings a and different coloring to make it out for the ozone-layer. Then,
apply a *good* and *realistic* Imagemap created for spherical mapping to
make it out for the earth. Now, apply the same map as bumpmap (the best
thing would be to edit the colormap into greyscales and then soften the
oceanic areas to prevent bumps there).

- If you like, I have rendered a planet that goes along with most planets
rendered using Lightwave.

 o
