@node IML-333 " MSG-333  Subject: Modeling Black Holes
@toc contents

Subject: Modeling Black Holes
Date:    Tuesday, 12 December 1995 17:35:59 
From:    lund@hoa.ping.dk (Anders Lundholm)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

CC: DAVEH47@delphi.com

Letter from Anders Lundholm to Dave Hardenbrook Written 11 Dec 95 At 22:23:58
O'clock

Hi Dave ...

 DH> Since black holes are really not "holes" at all, but collapsed stars
 DH> from which no light can escape, just use a primitive sphere that is
 DH> Totally black :)

All this blackhole stuff made me hooked up on creating one my self. It
turned out so realistic that I was about to be sucked into cyberspace
severaltimes when viewing my renderings! :)

 I created a form in the the formseditor looking like an hyberbolic
subtractor. To this, I applied the cyclone texture from Essence-II twice
(each with different sizes and a bit more bluish to add noise etc).
Furthermore, I cloned the subtractor and applied a nice static attribute
using the electric (remember to set the mix/morph to 1.0) texture + Ghost.
I rendered a 500 frame animation (720x576) and put it on my Vlab (realtime
playback!) <drooling>

Now, If anyone wants the object \ project (20kb) or an Image from the
sequence lemme know!

 DH> On the other hand, if you want something a little more dramatic, like a
 DH> black hole surrounded by an "accretion disk", I suggest putting your black
 DH> sphere at the center of a disk or nearly flat cylinder and map a
 DH> paint-program-produced multi-colored spiral to the disk.

 This won't work when the camera gets close. The pixels will disturb all
realism present. However, to simulate a realistic black hole, use a
CSG-sphere and add .1 to the fog-lenght and apply the ghost-texture. Play
around with the settings and *Capow*, you have a real working blak hole!

 Letter sponsored by Nilfish!

 o
/#\  Anders Lundholm . Alien Workshop (Tm) . Lund@Hoa.Ping.Dk
 ZZ Computer Graphics Design . 3D Modeling & Animation

-- Via Xenolink 1.97, XenolinkUUCP 1.1

