@node IML-335 " MSG-335  Subject: Re: Attachments and Advertisements
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Attachments and Advertisements
Date:    Tuesday, 12 December 1995 18:23:45 
From:    jprusins@cybergrafix.com (John Prusinski)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


>On the same token, (Helmy, you can stop reading here) some I'm sure 
>appreciate the offers of objects and such at a cost; others may not.  I 
>would say I am of the latter persuasion.  I have always viewed this list 
>as sort of a two way Public Broadcast System rather than cable.  If 
>somebody needs a tutorial or a specific object or texture they can ask 
>for it. 

I'd have to disagree with this... while I'm personally not going to take 
advantage of Helmy's offer at the present time, I think this list is the 
perfect place to spread information like this.  For one thing, if someone 
wants to start a service like this, they have to let potential customers 
know about it, and advertising in print is expensive enough that it would 
have to raise the cost of the product substantially.  This particular offer 
is aimed specifically at Imagine users, and that's a small enough universe 
that it's like using buckshot to take out a mosquito to advertise even in 
mainstream 3D publications.  Also, the service he's offering is potentially 
of value to Imagine users (i.e., the IML).  While I don't have enough need 
for a random selection of objects to come pouring in every month at this 
point, it's certainly not inconceivable that at some point I'll have a rush 
commercial job, need an object in a hurry, and remember that there's someone 
out there reachable by email who has a pretty large library of everyday 
objects in Imagine format... that kind of info could be worth it's weight in 
gold!

As far as I'm concerned, anybody who wants to post offers of commercial 
services or goods specifically targeted at the Imagine user is welcome to 
drop them in my mailbox at any time!

John.
