I've been using the Canon for a while, and I'm really happy with it.  With 
the (expensive!) glossy paper you get output which is hard to tell from 
photographic, particularly if you "res-up" the graphic to 300 dpi or so 
before printing.  The output is also pretty good on plain paper, which is 
very useful for proofing or for client approvals.

John.
