@node IML-341 " MSG-341  Subject: Re: Win95 trouble...help
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Win95 trouble...help
Date:    Tuesday, 12 December 1995 19:33:29 
From:    NancyJcbs@aol.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

In a message dated 95-12-12 11:23:53 EST, you write:

>I have a problem, it seems like that the ms-dos on win95 having dificulty
>runing 
>Imagine4.0.
>Got win95 installed on my P90.


Hi Tom,
You haven't said exactly what problems you are having running 
Imagine under WIN 95, so I'll just list what I do that works,
and you can use anything out of this that helps .
Also, if anyone else is newly firing up Imagine on Win95, 
perhaps this will benefit.

Here's the way I have configured WIN95 for Imagine (or vice versa).
First, I discovered, because you cant turn off DPMI in Win95 , 
that you can't use a DOS window for Imagine.
You have to use MSDOS Mode to run it. But it works well for me.
You have to remember, however, that if you are using a 
Win95-dependant compression scheme (like Drivespace), you 
won't be able to use the compressed disks from DOS mode.

BTW,this configuration seems also to make maximum ram free.

PROCEDURE:
I made a (desktop, icon) shortcut for Imagine in the usual manner.

Then, right click on the icon 
      and go to properties, program, advanced.
Check the box for MS DOS Mode. 
The entry spaces for config.sys and autoexec.bat will become active.
Below are the full configurations I use for these.
Some of the commands are specific to my setup, because I need to 
load a syquest driver for DOS, and I wanted to have the option 
to use my tablet,or not. (it's EXCELLENT for modelling, kind of a 
pain for menu use). Explanations are in [brackets] -
you will obviously choose to leave some of these lines out because you 
probably don't need them, but I thought to include them in case anyone 
who reads this may find the reference useful.

CONFIG.SYS for MS-DOS mode:

DOS=HIGH,UMB
Device=C:\WINDOWS\Himem.Sys
DEVICE=c:\syquest\sqatdrvr.sys        [syquest driver]

AUTOEXEC.BAT for MS-DOS mode:

SET CONFIG=Windows
SET winbootdir=C:\WINDOWS     [my windows dir. location]
SET SOUND=C:\SB16             [soundblaster]
choice /t:n,10 use tablet     [chooser (y/n) to 
if errorlevel==2 goto :mouse             load driver
d:\caldb\ccmouse /c2                  for either
goto :done                            ....
:mouse                                        ...
c:\mouse\mouse                                ....
:done                                 tablet or mouse]
d:                            [drive and directory where 
cd \imagine                           I have Imagine]

Be sure to save the configuration.(OK twice)

Now, when you hit the Imagine Icon, your computer will
reboot with the above configurations and go directly
to Imagine. When you quit, it will go back to Win95.

Hope there's something in here that helps.

Nancy


                       @{"           Thread          360" link IML-360}
                       @{"  -=> RETURN TO CONTENTS!<=-  " link contents}
@endnode


