@node IML-346 " MSG-346  Subject: Re:Win95 trouble...help
@toc contents

Subject: Re:Win95 trouble...help
Date:    Tuesday, 12 December 1995 23:02:38 
From:    El Guapo! <fubar@netcom.com>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


The Dos compatibility mode has to reboot anyway ( I think)
Which means you would have to boot up in windows, then 
reboot for imagine.  If your starting up and just want
to go into imagine, hit F8 when you first see the WIN95
screen.  This will gibve you the boot up menu and you 
can chose "8. Previous Version".  Which should dump you
to a C: prompt just like you had befor windows 95 ever
came along.

If you in windows 95 mode you notice that there is a pair
of files called config.dos and autoexec.dos -- theses are
the alternate files that get loaded when you start in 
"Previous version" mode. (so you could make them custom to 
an imagine setup).  When you boot up in "Previous Version" 
these files show up as config.sys and autoexec.bat ( not 
..dos).

You should be able to have it both ways.

Cris <fubar@netcom.com>

