Subject: Advertisements and the Like
Date:    Wednesday, 13 December 1995 00:20:21 
From:    Charles Blaquiere <blaq@io.org>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

Although I'm generally opposed to unsolicited commercial messages on the 
Net, I feel that helmy's product fits exactly within this list's topic 
(Imagine), and that few will ever follow in his footsteps and market 
commercial products for the Imagine crowd. As a result, I feel an 
occasional Imagine-related ad would be more valuable information than 
irritation. I'm all for it, with, say, a one-mailing-a-month limit.

> From: C and/or A Sullivan <ctromanh@uoguelph.ca>
> 
> why don't you start a new mailing list and let people here know it exists
> and anyone who wants it can subscribe.

What's the difference between putting messages on the IML advertising 
his object subscription service, and messages advertising his object 
subscription mailing list?

