>It could create a photorealistic planet using textures, if not Earth
>specifically, if we consider scenes which are purely mathematically
>generated 'not cheating'.
>
>Long live 'cheating'!!<<

I have created some really nice planets with textures only.  Imagine is
unsurpassed in that area.  Personally I think any program utilized to create
an image or post processing of some effect is quite acceptable if it gives
you a final result you are happy with.  I know purists like Steve Blackmon
and GreG tsadillas rarely use maps other than for bump mapping but I don't
have the intuitive sense of the textures that they posess.  I do find as time
goes on that it gets more and more intuitve however.  I have on occasion
applied 5 and 6 textures trying to get to a final result and achieving it
because it seemed like they were the right ones to utilize in a particular
order.  Many times it takes allot of experimentation however which is
something I do a great deal more of since getting the pentium.

