@node IML-360 " MSG-360  Subject: Re: Win95 trouble...help
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Win95 trouble...help
Date:    Wednesday, 13 December 1995 00:46:40 
From:    Chris Hall <chris.hall@dial.pipex.com>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

At 02:43 PM 12/12/95 +0200, you wrote:
>Hi guys
>
>I have a problem, it seems like that the ms-dos on win95 having dificulty
runing 
>Imagine4.0.
>Got win95 installed on my P90.
>I dont know what the problem is, and it might be that I'm a bit nerdy when it 
>comes to pc's.
>Any help apriciated
>
>Tom Renderbrandt
>
If you installed it over the top of your previous dos and windows get hold
of a copy of a program called Tweak UI from www.microsoft.com in the win95
free stuff bit (I think). Using this you can set up your PC to allow you to
boot into your OLD dos when you start up and run imagine as you used to.
Just press F4 when the "Starting windows 95" line comes up. Of course you
must have kept your old system files when you installed. This is how I work
it and it's great. It avoids rebooting the machine every time I quit out to
do something else.

Chris Hall.

