@node IML-365 " MSG-365  Subject: Tip: QuickEdges
@toc contents

Subject: Tip: QuickEdges
Date:    Wednesday, 13 December 1995 01:02:25 
From:    Charles Blaquiere <blaq@io.org>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

> From: Anders Lundholm <lund@hoa.ping.dk>
> 
> 2. Pick_Select/pick Range (1,100321,10) this will pick every 10. edge in
>    the object.

Agreed, a great tip. It gives your object a cloudy quality, like a group 
of black flies in August. As an addendum to your tip, one can also use 
Imagine's Edge Filter to automatically pick edges that outline 
significant features, then make those Quick Edges. After creating an 
object, making a set of representative Quick Edges is a real treat for 
me. The resulting display lets me pretend I'm on a Silicon Graphics 
workstation.


