@node IML-371 " MSG-371  Subject: Imagine 4 stuff
@toc contents

Subject: Imagine 4 stuff
Date:    Wednesday, 13 December 1995 04:02:56 
From:    lund@hoa.ping.dk (Anders Lundholm)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

CC: bwinter@inet.uni-c.dk

Letter from Anders Lundholm to Barry Winter Written 12 Dec 95 At 22:11:17
O'clock

Hi Barry ...

 BW> I would disagree the Amiga is much faster. My A4000 with a warpengine
 BW> is much slower than a P90, especially when working with 256 colours on =
 BW> screen.

 I use an 060\50Mhz and the CyberVision 64 bit Card from Phase5, 256 colors
in 1280 x 1024 is twice the speed than 256 colors in 640x480 on the PC.
This, with IBM's newest graphicscard on a 90Mhz Pentium.

 The only thing that bothers me, is the lame non-showing animations in the
camerawindow and the need of constant redrawing the editingarea. However,
the speed makes it easily up for most Pc's I've seen.

 As for renderingspeed, my setup does 20% faster renderings using textures
than an 90Mhz Pentium (same antialias setups) and about 5% using textures.

 o
