@node IML-397 " MSG-397  Subject: Anyone using Maxon's Cinema 4D for Amiga?
@toc contents

Subject: Anyone using Maxon's Cinema 4D for Amiga?
Date:    Wednesday, 13 December 1995 13:55:00 
From:    JoBrozycki@vaxsar.vassar.edu (John Brozycki)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

I realize this is the IMAGINE mailing list but, nevertheless, I'm curious if
anyone here has used or is using Maxon's Cinema 4D for the Amiga (especially
you folks in Europe) and if so, what you think of it?

I requested the demo from Oregon Research (they'll be distributing it here
in the U.S.) a while back and haven't really heard anything about it since.
It doesn't appear to have all the power/versatility of Imagine but has a
neat interface and has low system requirements.  The provided sample outputs
looked pretty good, but the demo is pretty severely crippled- I could only
get it to render a tiny wireframe screen- so I don't know how fast/well it
actually renders.  Anyway, if it's quick and easy to set things up it might
fill a niche for simple things that might be more cumbersome in Imagine.

Thanks,

John Brozycki
JoBrozycki@vassar.edu


