@toc contents

Subject: Re:Win95 trouble...help
Date:    Wednesday, 13 December 1995 14:29:38 
From:    jbarela@melpar.esys.com (John Barela - UC Test)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

El Guapo! <fubar@netcom.com> writes:

> The Dos compatibility mode has to reboot anyway ( I think)
> Which means you would have to boot up in windows, then 
> reboot for imagine.  If your starting up and just want
> to go into imagine, hit F8 when you first see the WIN95
> screen.  This will gibve you the boot up menu and you 
> can chose "8. Previous Version".  Which should dump you
> to a C: prompt just like you had befor windows 95 ever
> came along.

Or you could hit F4 and skip the menu and boot directly 
into your old version of Dos. Both these methods assume 
you have installed Win95 with dual boot capability. Dual
boot is not neccessarily the default installation.

Imagine will run on Dos 7.0 though. (Dos "ver" command actually 
returns "Windows 95 Dos Version 4.0" or something like that)

John


