  Well I've some tips for all the win95 users.
      - You can start a ms-dos 7.0 session if you type in "mode co80" whe the
      message "You can turn off your system" appears into the screen.
      - There is a file named MSDOS.SYS. This a hidden system read-only file.
      You can edit with a text editor this file and in the line that says
      "BOOTGUI=1" change 1 by 0 and voila! the next time your system starts
      you must type in "win" to start the gui and all of those new features 
      like long names ...

