@node IML-407 " MSG-407  Subject: Re[2]: DOS vs. NT (was: Re: Toystory info / NT version)
@toc contents

Subject: Re[2]: DOS vs. NT (was: Re: Toystory info / NT version)
Date:    Wednesday, 13 December 1995 16:13:36 
From:    spack@mv.us.adobe.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

     
>The NT Kernal is >HUGE<  (if you play M:tG, read the flavour text for 
>Polar Kraken to understand what I'm talking about)... if you're running 
>NT, the kernal takes up over 16MB of RAM _by itself_... read: if you 
>have 8MB of RAM, the OS has to swap out parts of itself, just to run... 
>this 'swapping out' (which doesn;t happen in the DOS version at all) 
>degrades performance by an ungodly amount (hard drive seek times are 
>measured in milliseconds, RAM seek times are measured in nanoseconds...)
     
     Wrong!  The NT kernal takes 2-4Mb.  How could NT even run if it had to 
     swap out parts of itself!  You can run NT with as little as 12Mb, but 
     it is painful.
     
     -Scott
