I agree, the show movie on the PC is a little jerky. Its smooth on the 
Amiga and can be full screen. I did like the fact that I could start 
Imagine on the PC in the same interface as the Amiga. Its the only 
program I have seen that is the same across platforms (mostly). If we had 
an optimized 040/060 version then I would be very happy. I like the 
better memory management ,true multitasking and compatiability on the Amiga.
I have many more problems using the PC for anything, not just one product.
Who started the "compatiable" term on the PC anyway.
I'm not knocking the PC, I just get very frustrated when I use them.
Amiga user's are spoiled!
My 50mhz Amiga with 18 megs ram IS FASTER and can handle larger projects 
than my P90 32 megs ram.

just a fact no flame intended.

Waiting on a 32bit TRUE multitasking OS, slick and bugfree GUI, great 
memory managemant, software that is compatiable, True plug n play devices
new fast processor 68060
take a look at an Amiga, its all been there for over 10 years

I own several PC's and Amiga's. before you flame me, you should have some 
Amiga experience to compare to.



