@node IML-412 " MSG-412  Subject: Re: Magnet
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Magnet
Date:    Wednesday, 13 December 1995 18:59:15 
From:    Kevin Alvarado <kra@Rocky.aesthetic.com>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

> I know this must be a very simple thing for you guys, bun no matter how I
> try, picking ponts, faces or whatever, can't find out how to use magnet.
> The manuale doesn't say how to use it at all, It only says that the mouse
> becomes a magnet, but doesn't say what to press or pick. Can sombody
> tellme a little tut to use magnet!

You need to be in "Drag Points" mode and have the magnet set to on.  After
that, just click & drag points as you would by draging points normaly.  If
there is a specific point you want to move but can't get to it in one view,
click on it in another view and hold the shift key.  Go into the view you want
to move the points in and release the shift key, then drag away.

-KV-

