@node IML-429 " MSG-429  Subject: Simple lights on a plane
@toc contents

Subject: Simple lights on a plane
Date:    Thursday, 14 December 1995 04:50:57 
From:    RobSampson@aol.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

It still never ceases to amaze me how some of the simpler things in Imagine
can produce such nice effects.  While working on a scene with a filter
decaled object I found myself in need of a backdrop during some of the
quickrenders while I was tweaking it.  I placed a plane primitive behind the
objects and dropped the default light in favour of three axis with lite
attributes set to rgb 255,155,155 point and diminish intensity.  The effect
of the lights on the white backdrop made me stop working on the object I was
creating and start experimenting with the lights and plane primitive in trace
mode as it's own project.  My first impression was of something like a Close
Encounters space ship coming towards me.  I intend to try it with some of the
lighting textures like caustic.itx ect and see how that works as well.  It's
really simple to set up so take a look.  Some nice glowing lights effects for
a backdrop in some other image perhaps.

Bob.............
