@node IML-448 " MSG-448  Subject: PC TTF Fonts to DXF Converter
@toc contents

Subject: PC TTF Fonts to DXF Converter
Date:    Thursday, 14 December 1995 13:47:46 
From:    That bloke from HMS <tobs@perihelion.co.uk>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

Hi Imagineers,

Just thought you'd like to know of a handy util called font3d (sorry
PC only !) which runs in DOS and converts a given piece of text for a
given font to DXF format (which can then be loaded into Imagine).

It also supports the formats RAW, POV, Vivid 2.0 and RenerMan RIB,
various options also include bevelled edges and applying textures
(unfortunately these do not apply to the DXF format B-( ).

It can be obtained from -

   ftp://x2ftp.oulu.fi/pub/msdos/programming/utils/f3d150.zip

I could uuencode a copy to you if you want it, its 320k zipped.

Also, on the subject of fonts <ducking> where can I get some PS fonts ?
I'm sure this has been mentioned before but I reckon I must have been
a bit ambitious on the good old delete key !! Web search for
'Postscript' is very "interesting" B-((((.

Lastly, can someone remind me how to move the axis of an object
without moving the object itself B-/ ? (ie without going into
the Transformations requester and checking 'Transform axis only'),
this time I'll tatoo it to my left hand ...

Regards

Toby

