Date:    Thursday, 14 December 1995 17:18:11 
From:    RobSampson@aol.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

In a message dated 95-12-14 09:59:11 EST, you write:

>I'm using imagine 3.0 and can't read none of the meshes i export to DXF
>from 3D Studio, It works in the other way though. Is this normal?!
>
>Have a nice day! :)

I had a similar problem with AcadR13.  Imagines DXF files were acceptable in
Acad, but Acad's dxf export would not read into Imagine.  I got around it by
exporting in 3DS format from Acad and then converting the 3DS file to
Imagine's object format using 3ds2im by Andrey Ziemisky <sp>.  I have found
this utility to be excellent in converting all the 3ds objects I have come
across, and there are many more of them out there than Imagine format
objects.

Bob.............
Imagine renderings.
