@node IML-470 " MSG-470  Subject: Re: FW: RE: SV: Windows etc
@toc contents

Subject: Re: FW: RE: SV: Windows etc
Date:    Friday, 15 December 1995 00:46:45 
From:    David Alan Steiger <das@altair.csustan.edu>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

On Thu, 14 Dec 1995 bob_landry@corp.Cubic.COM wrote:

> >If you render in 24bit you only need to render one palette, at the start of a
n Imagine session. 
> >Then just tell it to use previous palette. What's the problem?
> 
> I think the point here is if you are rendering in 24bits then why do I need a 
palette at all. 24 bit
> images don't use palettes!

I assume it is calculating the dispay palette for the 'show image' button 
on the Project screen.  That way it wouldn't have to calculate it every 
time you showed it.  It seems to display too quickly for palette 
calculation on the fly.  

Of course, if your viewmode is displaying 24bit, no generation should ever
be necessary.

Dave


