@node IML-472 " MSG-472  Subject: Planetary pics.
@toc contents

Subject: Planetary pics.
Date:    Friday, 15 December 1995 01:21:25 
From:    spencer@lowell.edu (John R. Spencer)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

Here are some Imagine pictures with planetary themes, to be found
on my Web page at http://www.lowell.edu/users/spencer/Welcome.html

1) An Imagine 4.0-generated Christmas card, a "still life" with
a bowl of fruit and planets.  4.0 soft shadows are used,
and the apple has a subtle but realistic streaking done with the "Iris"
texture, which unfortunately is mostly lost in conversion to 256
colors.

2) An illustration for our book "The Great Comet Crash" (plug,
plug...), of the mess that the impact of one of the fragments of comet
Shoemaker-Levy 9 would have made on our planet, had it hit us
instead of Jupiter.  I made a transparency map of a Hubble image of 
the impact scar on Jupiter and wrapped it, to scale, over a
globe with an Earth color map applied.

3) An illustration of Jupiter's magnetosphere for the same book,
using a fog object to show the ring and sheet of plasma ejected from
the moon Io.  A yellow glow representing the cloud of sodium
that also surrounds Io was added in "post-production"- I couldn't
do it as a separate fog object, because of artifacts produced 
by overlapping fog objects.

Comments welcome!
John Spencer

