@node IML-480 " MSG-480  Subject: Re: PAR
@toc contents

Subject: Re: PAR
Date:    Friday, 15 December 1995 05:03:54 
From:    Curtcee@aol.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

<From:        sgiff@airmail.net (Stephen Gifford)

<I was wondering if someone knows what the correct aspect ratio from
<Rendering from Imagine to the PAR.  I am using a PC.  Thanks

I've always used 1:1 as the aspect ratio. I was under the impression it was
the only aspect ratio to use for video.

Slightly off the subject: A thunderstorm hit here in California the other day
and a lightning bolt hit a power pole a few blocks from my house. ( I was
staring out the window at the time and place where it hit. Between the flash
and the bone-rattling explosion I realized that I NEVER want to be that close
to a lightning hit again.) Anyway, I was rendering in Imagine at the time. Of
course the power died with the lightning hit and my only concern (well,
besides my concern for the people who lived next to that power pole) was
whether I had 1) anything left of my rendering, and 2) anything left of my
PC. After the power came back on, the rendering was just fine and the PC
showed absolutely no ill effects. Until I tried to use my modem. Apparently,
a spike found it's way through the phone line and fried my modem sunny side
up. Moral of story: Always unplug phone cable when modem not in use.

Curtis
Curtcee@aol.com


                       @{"           Thread          495" link IML-495}
                       @{"  -=> RETURN TO CONTENTS!<=-  " link contents}
@endnode


@node IML-481 " MSG-481  Subject: RE:Strata
@toc contents

Subject: RE:Strata
Date:    Friday, 15 December 1995 06:51:10 
From:    Granberg Tom <tom.granberg@TV2.no>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

m.rubin9@genie.com:
>Has anyone on the list used current versions of StrataPro enough to
>venture a comparison of features with Imagine 4.0?
>
>I only spent a few minutes with it a year ago and need to respond to
>"criticism" at my school that we should move to Strata rather than
>Imagine.
>
>Strata certainly has a much slicker interface, and it seems to have
>comparable tools, but I'm not sure of their actual ease of use and
>I've heard it renders very slowly. The latest release has some kind
>of spline modelling and VRML output.
>
>Floater
>
I'd played a little with it, and I should be a little careful here, but you have
 
several reasons why you should go for Imagine.

You say "slick" interface, and I say clutered workspace. There is always a 
difficulty when working with icons/images that is supposed to tell you what you 

are doing, but most of the time they are only confusing.

Imagine compared to Strata is quite good, ofcourse I would like to have 3d 
splines when moddeling, and alpha channels, but apart from that Imagine is a far 
more powerfull package partly due to it's rendering engine and texture support 
and mapping tools. It's modelling tools, awsome, I mean it, awsome.

I have seen some of the stuff come out of strata, and they are good, but in a 
hand of a skilled pro' any package could reproduse stuning imagery.

If you choose Strata, you choose Mac,witch in my mind for 3d is a dead 
end......unless it exists on other platforms, witch I dont think it does.

With Imagine you get a hell of a lot more bang for your buck, and you could 
invest the money on fast pc hardware.

And the rendering time on Strata with every button turned on......doh, sloooow.

Just some toughts about it

Later

Renderbrandt

