@node IML-487 " MSG-487  Subject: Re: To Rob Sampson
@toc contents

Subject: Re: To Rob Sampson
Date:    Friday, 15 December 1995 08:18:18 
From:    RobSampson@aol.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

In a message dated 95-12-15 01:10:21 EST, you write:

> I was wondering which textures you used on the big red ship in
fighters.jpg.
>And what the settings are.

Thanks for the words Mikael.  That particular ship was one of my earlier
creations and utilizes only one texture (dethstar).  The attributes were as
follows..
Color 125,55,30
Reflect 0,0,0
Filter 0,0,0
Spec 135,65,40
Hardness 42
rough 0
shininess 0
bright 0
refr index 1.0
fog lenght 0
Texture Dethstar
x,y,z size 20,20,20 adjust to preference
x,y,z, eccentricity 1.69,1.69,1.69
bevel width .1
bump adjust -0.9
red bevel color -0.9
green 0
blue 0
bevel reflect -0.9
bevel filter -0.9
dirt 0
rust 0

That was it.  Since then I have found that incorporating other textures with
dethstar can produce some nice stuff.  Marble elongated along an axis can
produce nice rust streaking (so who cares you don't get rust in space:),
blast can be adjusted to splotch a surface or make carbon exhaust streaking.
 And although it was not available when I made this particular ship, don't
discount candyapple at least for a look see when you have everything done.
 It can sometime really enhance a look at times.  What is nice is that it
requires no adjustment and can be dumped easily if the quick render does not
look right with it.

Bob.............
Imagine renderings.
http://home.aol.com/robsampson




