@node IML-516 " MSG-516  Subject: No more IML.... No true alternatives either.
@toc contents

Subject: No more IML.... No true alternatives either.
Date:    Friday, 15 December 1995 20:35:46 
From:    jacob@altair.csustan.edu (Dave Jacob)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


Well, after the 3 megaton nuclear device going off here this morning,
no one should the repercussions to be any less devestating, I guess.
What we are left with is truly a mess of high proportion, and no
real way to pick up the pieces. I can understand Dave's response to 
close the list down. I would probably have done the same, and so would
you--especially if the alternative would be to be considered 
as responsible for the actions of a warez pirate. The list as a 
free, unmoderated, forum could survive our opinions, bitchings,
and dreams, but not a monumentally stupid, not even to mention not legal, act as

as what just happened.

(I am trying to remain 'diplomatic' here)

All that's left is to determine where we can go form here. Unfortunately,
I just dont see *any* real replacement for this list. While a 
Impulse created web site is a nice development, and really needed, I 
just can not see it replacing this list. Something tells me there
could be no spontaineaty in such a rigidly controlled environment. 
Downloading bug patches, yes, contacting staff, yes. But getting
advice from other users, in their own words, without expletives
deleted? Nope. 

A newsgroup isn't the answer either. Its like watching a TV talk show--
observer oriented: you know you can call in, but how many of us do? Most
wont bother, because posting to a newsgroup isnt as direct, immediate,
or useful. The 'flavor' isnt the same as a direct mailing list. Also,
you can bet the even more uncontrolled atmosphere of a newsgroup will
lead to the massave posting of binaries -- of all kinds. And a
moderated newsgroup will not work for the same reasons the Impulse 
web site wont work. 

I mean, if we Imagine users were 'white shirt and tie" types, we'd all
be using 3-D Studio, right ...?  ;)

So whats the solution? I just dont know.  Its too bad there isn't 
a solution for human stupidity. We wouldn't be having this discussion. Damn.


Dave.

                       @{"           Thread          525" link IML-525}
                       @{"  -=> RETURN TO CONTENTS!<=-  " link contents}
@endnode


