How many users are actually on the list?  I know it would be a lot of 
work for everyone but I've seen local interest groups do this.  Make an 
address book entry with everybody's name in it and everyone on the list 
will be responsible for taking care of their own list.  Unfortunately it 
would put a large overhead on each message but at least we'd still be in 
contact until a more viable alternative comes along.  If someone 
unsubscribes everyone would have to edit their address book 
individually.  I know it's not a real solution but it's a bandage at 
short notice.  So if you're for that post a message with subject ADDRESS 
so those who care to can grab the address and put it in their address 
book at least temporarily.  If somebody recruits a new member then they 
can post a SUBSCRIBE message to everyone and include the new persons 
address which everyone can individually add to their address book.  If we 
do this quickly we can try it out before the list goes down.  Thoughts?


