@node IML-535 " MSG-535  Subject: Response to a response
@toc contents

Subject: Response to a response
Date:    Saturday, 16 December 1995 02:22:57 
From:    Valleyview@aol.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

No more IML - Merry Christmas

(large sigh) My feelings and opinions on the future:

I'm for a newsgroup as a replacement for the IML. We need something to
continue what get accomplished here and my guess is that Impulse's mailing
list won't satisfy a lot of people. This is nothing negative against Impulse,
I am just sure it will not be what people are used to here.

I've just recently subscribed to the Real3d mailing list. It is run by
RealSoft and closely moderated. They seem to be fairly strict with what can
be posted, as a matter of fact they just posted that there shouldn't be any
more gripes about features or wishlists or suggestions to the company. There
reasoning was that they have a big enough new features list that will take
years to do them. No computer wars, pyramid schemes, name calling, etc. (good
things)  Probably less input from users because company people are very
active in responding to posts. This probably intimidates some people from
responding due to fear of making a fool of themselves. (and we're so good at
it):) They have a lot less posts probably because of a stricter structure. If
you have a tech problem, you get a good answer right now. This is good or
bad, your choice.

From what Mike has said to me, I'm sure the new list will be just as strict
if not more. Real3d does have an ftp site for objects, tutorials, images,
etc. I hope Impulse does the same. We all know how Impulse follows a strict
schedule so I would plan on being without a mailing list for more then a
month or two, so if we can get something else going now, let's do it!

Rick 

