Unfortunate the IML will be going away.  A site or list moderated by Impulse
won't be nearly as robust.  It will infact be essentially censored since I'm
sure Halvorson won't tolerate even the mildest critisism of Imagine.  I'd go
as far as to say that Impulse will probably treat new feature suggestions as
critisisms.  All because some bozo thinks it's ok to distribute software.  It
certainly was no mistake, there is too much work involved to encode and send
a package like this.  As I understand it, Lightwave has a dongle on the
parallel port.  I suppose now I wish Imagine had one as well.  Then at least
we would not be in this position.  I don't render for money.  My only reason
for creating the stuff that I do is to read that occasional post from someone
who really liked someting I created.  It's rare, but it is enough.  The other
joy was discovering this list.  Sandwiched in between all the really
entertaining side bars that go on there would be an occasional jewel which
provided some insight or inspiration for a new scene to be created.  I hope
somebody who has the knowhow and resources to keep this list going does so.
