@node IML-554 " MSG-554  Subject: Impulse Web Site
@toc contents

Subject: Impulse Web Site
Date:    Saturday, 16 December 1995 12:06:23 
From:    Ted Stethem <tstethem@linknet.kitsap.lib.wa.us>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

  The problem with web sites are that they usually aren't all that 
interactive, at least between various visitors to them. Commercial web sites 
are more like product showcases or catalogs. Plus, they tend to remain 
fixed in design for several months at a time.
  As for an Impulse web site, it definitely won't be there as an 
inter-user forum. I could see them advertising Imagine there, and God 
knows, they need better advertising.  But the indirect announcement (you 
notice that all this talk about an Impulse website is coming second-hand, 
not a direct announcement to the list?) is coming from a company that 
less than two years ago was saying they didn't know how to get on the 
Internet and didn't understand how to ftp (their reason for not sending 
examples of their work to Aminet).
  This is all from a couple of years ago. If you go back far enough, and 
the IML archives are complete, you will see quoted messages from Mike 
Halvorson saying, "Yeah, they (Impulse) had looked at a Windows version 
but it slowed rendering down too much."  Think about it, Impulse has 
known about the PC expanded memory problem with Imagine since V2.0. And 
it is still there in V4.0!  Do you really naively believe this is a responsive 
company?!!?
  Some things have changed over at Impulse. And Imagine does have a lot 
of neat new features. Who knows, maybe things can change for the better. 
I hope somebody can put together an Imagine newsgroup.  It is the users, 
you all, that really make Imagine such a powerful 3D program. It is those 
people that have the tenacity to overcome the limitations of the 
documentation, the perserverence to experiment endlessly with modeling, 
texturing, and lighting techniques, the brain talent to write new 
textures, and the generosity to pass those labors on to others that 
really made this list worthwhile.

                       @{"           Thread          358" link IML-358}
                       @{"  -=> RETURN TO CONTENTS!<=-  " link contents}
@endnode


