On Wed, 13 Dec 1995, Duncan wrote:

> Hello, Barry.
> 
> >> Is there a way to bypass the palatte generation. I use 24bit boards and 
> >> files. Why does there have to be a palatte?
> >> 
> >> Just tell it to use previous palette, the first render you do per session
>    will generate one, after that it wont.
> 
>     Is 'Render First' an Amiga thing ??
> 
> -- 
> 
>  dunc@eraser.demon.co.uk 
> 

Just make sure the first frame isn't totally black.  I made that mistake 
once only to find 5 hours of rendering time later that my animation was 
just a black screen.

If your opening screen is black, then you could always render one of the 
frames in the animation that has the most colour and then specify that as 
the pallette file.


   Rick H.



