Yaaaaaay!!!

Good news.  Kinda glad we don't need my crappy idea.  Anyway here's 
something that may be of interest to some.

"THE MIND'S EYE" PRODUCER LAUNCHES WORLDWIDE 

CALL FOR COMPUTER ANIMATION

Steven Churchill, Producer of "THE MIND'S EYE", "BEYOND THE
MIND'S EYE" and "THE GATE TO THE MIND'S EYE", the immensely
popular series of computer animation videos, and the award
winning "COMPUTER ANIMATION FESTIVAL" series of home-videos,
announced plans for the most ambitious series of computer
animated video and CD-ROM titles in "hi-tech" history.  "To make
these titles we need more high quality 3-D computer animation
than ever before," says Churchill, who has used a $75 million
library of computer animation to produce nine videos and three
CD-ROM titles.  "There are thousands of talented computer
animators out there and we want to see their work," he
continues.  "If it's good enough, we'll pay the artist a
generous royalty and show his or her work to millions of
computer animation fans around the world."

"Half of all the net revenues of each project are shared by the
artists," explains Churchill, who is the Founder and President
of Odyssey Productions, a San Diego based video production
company. "This has added up to a substantial amount of royalties
for pre-existing animation", Churchill points out.  "It is truly
found money.  'The Mind's Eye' is still selling well after more
than four years in the market.  The 'evergreen' sales of these
titles has enabled us to provide a steady royalty stream to the
animators.  And if that's not enough incentive," Steven adds,
"we make the end-credits like a mini demo-reel for each
individual animator or animation company, showing a clip from
their piece while their written credits are displayed, so as to
maximize their exposure to the millions of people who view these
videos."

In 1990 Odyssey invited Miramar Productions to distribute and
also co-produce the hit video, "THE MIND'S EYE - A COMPUTER
ANIMATION ODYSSEY".  This video program is a powerful
combination of the world's best computer animation imagery
combined with a custom scored music soundtrack by James
Reynolds, creating a unique "Video Album".  Over 350,000 copies
have been sold to date, and it was on Billboard Magazine's video
sales charts for 30 weeks, reaching as high as #14 for all home
video sales in the U.S. 

In September 1992 the Odyssey/Miramar team completed the sequel
to "THE MIND'S EYE", which is titled "BEYOND THE MIND'S EYE". 
This stunning video program presents the latest computer
animation from around the world, with original music scored for
the video by Grammy award winning "Miami Vice" composer, Jan
Hammer.  Over 350,000 copies have been sold to date, and it was
on Billboard Magazine's video sales charts for 36 weeks,
reaching as high as #10.  It remained on Billboard's Music Video
charts for 108 weeks of continuous reporting.

Recently, Odyssey has produced four new videos:  "COMPUTER
ANIMATION FESTIVAL Vol.1",  which was released in April of 1993,
was designed to be the ultimate collection of 21 computer
animation short films, each shown in their entirety.  "VIRTUAL
NATURE", co-produced with Miramar, was released in November of
1993 and presents computer animation of nature and natural
scenery, set to original music.  "IMAGINARIA", also co-produced
with Miramar, was released in February of 1994 and is a special
collection of computer animation specifically assembled for
kids.  Finally, Odyssey has completed "COMPUTER ANIMATION
FESTIVAL Vol.2",  which was released May 24th 1994.  This is an
incredible collection of the 22 best new computer animation
short films, each shown in their entirety, including music
videos by Peter Gabriel and Todd Rundgren.

Odyssey entered into the world of interactive multimedia
programs in 1994 with the development of "THE COMPUTER ANIMATION
CATALOG".   It is an interactive video showcase of computer
animation artists on CD-ROM.  It was developed by Odyssey and
Tri-Digital Software for Microsoft's "JumpStart" program, a
multimedia developer's tool kit.

In October of 1994 Odyssey and Miramar released the spectacular
new video called "THE GATE TO THE MIND'S EYE", which is the
third in the "MIND'S EYE" series.  This all-new video album
presents the very latest computer animation from around the
world, with original music scored for the video by the world
renowned composer Thomas Dolby.  As of this date, over 150,000
copies have been sold, while it has been on Billboard's Music
Video charts for 40 weeks so far.

Most recently, Odyssey in conjunction with Tri-Digital Software,
is releasing two exciting CD-ROM titles.  "CYBERVISIONS" is an
entertaining and educational interactive anthology of 25 of the
greatest computer animation short films.  "FUTURE VISIONS SCREEN
SAVER" is a visually stunning collection of 25 different
computer animated screen savers.  

Odyssey is currently in production on eight new and exciting
video programs, including the fourth 

"MIND'S EYE" video.  Odyssey has just signed a new distribution
deal with Sony Music Video, who will be distributing all of the
new titles.  As part of Odyssey's pursuit of content for these
new videos, high-end computer animation of any style or type
will be seriously considered for inclusion.  Animators are
requested to send either VHS or 3/4" copies of their work to:


                                      Steven Churchill
                                      Odyssey Productions
                                      4413 Ocean Valley Lane
                                      San Diego, CA 92130

                                      (619) 793-1900 - Phone
                                      (619) 793-1942 - Fax
                                      odyssey@cts.com - E-mail

