@node IML-596 " MSG-596  Subject: The IML
@toc contents

Subject: The IML
Date:    Sunday, 17 December 1995 19:34:55 
From:    cjo@kiruna.se (Conny Joensson)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

Good Lord! That was CLOSE!!

I couldn't decide if I was going to start crying, hide under my bed or just
plain simply hurl myself out the window or from the top of the highest bridge
I could find (hmm, dunno if we have any high bridges in Kiruna... ah, well,
there's always the mine company's scy scraper).

Jeezes, just the thought of it: no more IML.
It sort of leaves an empty feeling in my guts (and I have got a lot of guts;)
Speaking of black holes...

Along with all the rest of you that have posted about this, I too must thank
Dave Wickard. I don't know him, have obviously never met the guy, and I am
still wondering what ever happened to his "Jurrasic Pork" animation...
************************************************
But I must direct a BIG WARM "THANK YOU" to him.
************************************************
I don't know where I would have been with Imagine if it wasn't for the IML.
Certainly I wouldn't have courage enough to put my own renderings on my
homepage, or on Aminet for that matter. I'd probably still be fiddling with
chrome spheres and chequered floors. Come to think of it... I am still
fiddling with spheres and floors...

And I couldn't agree more with Dave W when he says:
"I consider you all, far and near, my friends and comrades.
Thank you for sharing with me, your good humor, your hard fought knowledge,
your tips and your tutorials."

Don't you all get a lump in your throat?
H*ll, I consider some of you as close a friend as Mikael across the street, or
Peter down by the hospital, or Hans, or the other Mikael, or...
Even if some of you live on the other side of the globe!

Oh well, it would seem that it's been taken care of already. Thanks Perry!!!
I honestly don't know what I'd do without the IML and Charlie Blackears witty
remarks (and occasional tutorial;)

Right now all I need is a valium...

