@node IML-618 " MSG-618  Subject: Hail and Farewell
@toc contents

Subject: Hail and Farewell
Date:    Monday, 18 December 1995 12:17:14 
From:    gregory denby <gdenby@twain.helios.nd.edu>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


To Dave Wickard:
Thanks so much for handling the IML for so long.  Live long and render!

To Perry Lucas,
Thanks for salvaging the list.

All this brings up the IML charter.  Obviously, the list maintainer cannot
tolerate piracy or the appearance of piracy.  But is there any way a
repeat of the monster can be prevented without the list moderator
screening everything before transmission?  As much as I like tyhe list,
you'd have to pay me quite a lot to review everything.  Dave, if your
listening, what has Impulse said about all this, if anything?

At any rate, what I'd like to see in the future (an IML wish list):
Fast temporary un-subscribes, so that 300-500 pieces of mail don't
arrive during a vacation.  No uuencodes over 10K.

To 30,000 edges and beyond!
Greg Denby

                       @{"           Thread          751" link IML-751}
