  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

If you find the whole aawin.exe / aaplay.dll package, that will let you
script where it will play a sound file at the same time it shows your .flc.
 Avi files contain the .wav sound files in the same file with the animation.
If I remember right, the old windows media player let you convert between the
flcs and avis but the 95 version won't have anything to do with flcs. I
haven't used DTA but I have used VFD (video for dos) which is on AOL
somewhere and you can convert between the two or from stills. Next, there are
a lot of wav editors out there, free - share - commercial, to make your sound
files. The good ones let you view your pic on the top of the screen and your
sound scribblings on the bottom. You edit sound with cut and paste just like
graphics. Try Video for Windows too, it has a lot of editors in it. And it's
free.

Rick

