  I would prefer that UUencodes are not sent to the list as some users
pay for the download and storage of email.  To them, uuencodes are more
of a nuisence than a benefit.  The list is not meant to show work but
to discuss how to do it. 

  I wouldn't mind setting up an ftp site and/or an http site in the near 
future for such objects and images to be placed in one location in a
multitude of formats (jpg, gif, lzh, zip, etc.)  In fact, if we can get
imagine users to make some really nice images for a website, I can supply
the server space on my clients new t1 line.

  And before you ask, a listserv requires a dedicated computer for which
I can not afford yet.  Hence St. Johns University.

--Perry


