@node IML-650 " MSG-650  Subject: Re: Re:Helix
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Re:Helix
Date:    Monday, 18 December 1995 23:32:36 
From:    Kevin Alvarado <kra@Rocky.aesthetic.com>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

I dont mean to be ignorant, but what is a helix?

Tom
"I dont want to look it up"

A helix is a curve in 3D space that coils like a spring.  X and Y values of the
curve form a circle.  The Z values change with time.

( X, Y, Z ) values would have the functions:
( a*cos(t), a*sin(t), c*t)
were t varies with time.

I hope this explains it.

-- 
