@node IML-658 " MSG-658  Subject: Matrox and Imagine (was: PC Textures)
@toc contents

Subject: Matrox and Imagine (was: PC Textures)
Date:    Tuesday, 19 December 1995 04:01:16 
From:    Charles Blaquiere <blaq@io.org>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

> From: Andrew Nunn <apn@moby.demon.co.uk>
> 
> Also, has anyone that uses a Matrox Impression Plus card managed to get
> it to show 24 bit with Imagine?

I don't know about the Imp+, but I (and many others!) have the newer 
Millennium, and its VESA implementation is incompatible with Imagine. If 
you have a 2M WRAM card, Imagine will see 5 VESA modes; if, like me, you 
have the 4M model, Imagine sees no mode at all! The result is that I can 
only work in 640x480x16, and see quickrenders at 320x200x256. No 24-bit, 
no high-res editors, no texture playground, no realtime greyscale 
rendering peeking behind the editor screen!

The good news is that Matrox have been shipped a copy of Imagine, and 
will be checking it out. Keep your fingers crossed, people! In addition, 
the UniVESa folks are busy creating the next version of the popular 
program, which will support the Millennium. (Does the Imp+ use the same 
chipset?) So, there are two solutions in the pipeline.



                       @{"           Thread          691" link IML-691}
                       @{"  -=> RETURN TO CONTENTS!<=-  " link contents}
@endnode


