>Rob
> I have been using animator studio to add sound to Imagine animations and
>have been pretty pleased with it just make sure you get version 1.1, if you
>want to see how it works check out congaman avi in AOL animation library.
>Another benefit is that you can render your animations any size and they play
>in a custom sized window. Drawback is that the video codecs usually degrade
>the picture quality but its kind of adjustable.
>
>LuneEtun@aol.com
>

Slight correction here... the default AVI encoding that Animator Studio uses 
is RLE, basically lossless (which also results in fairly large file sizes), 
but it looks really good.  You also have the option of choosing one of the 
other standard lossy encoders (Microsoft, Indeo, Cinepak, etc.) with 
variable compression, or FLC.

John.

