>Pro) saved Imagine objects with ludicrous size values. I would load the 
>object into Detail and change its size (_object axes only_) to a 
>reasonable value. For example, use 32,32,32; you can then scale and 
>reposition the axes interactively if you want the bounding box to 
>faithfully represent the object. If you save the object, you 
>(theoretically) should have no problems at all.
>
>I believe under certain circumstances, Imagine will revert to default 
>size (32,32,32) in Action, and when applied to an object that had been 
>saved to disk with, say, 0.00001 Y size, the resulting figure in Stage 
>would appear 3,200,000 larger than in Detail. By setting the axes in the 
>saved-to-disk version of the object to something reasonable, those 
>settings should import without modification into Stage.
>
>Hopefully, this is reasonable, and I haven't been babbling on for the 
>last 5 minutes.


I've encountered this feature too.  Pixel3D either scales it up or down,
I don't recall which, by a factor of 10.

Jaeson K.
