@node IML-681 " MSG-681  Subject: Re: Stage FX & Shredder
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Stage FX & Shredder
Date:    Tuesday, 19 December 1995 12:47:49 
From:    jbk4@psu.edu (Prophet)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

>: As long as I switched from one stage fx to another, it works.  But
>: if I try repeating the same one consecutively, it doesn't.
>Can you make a more detailed step by step of your problem? 
>I use the Stage FX in detail with no problem at all and, in fact, i found that

>imagine remembers tha last values you give to the effect when re-apply it.

This regards the Amiga 4.0 version.

1.  In Detail Editor, Add a primitive Sphere.
2.  Apply a Stage FX, ripple.  
3.  Accept default settings.
4.  Pretend you don't like the result, UNDO
5.  Re-Appy ripple stage fx.
6.  change or accept default settings.

Nothing.  If I try consecutive applications of the SAME fx, it
doesn't work after the 1st one.  I've tried it with other fx
and the result was the same.

If we go back to step 5 and apply a NEW fx instead of ripple,
the new fx will work, but only once.  I can't apply it a 2nd time.
But if I go from the NEW fx back to ripple, ripple will work, but
only once.

This works:           This doesn't work:

  Ripple              Ripple
  Shred                       Ripple
  Ripple
  
I must load and APPLY the new fx in order to use the previous fx
again.  I tried just loading the new fx, hitting cancel, and then
loading the previous fx but it didn't work that way.

Jaeson K.
