> From: gmartin@mv.us.adobe.com
> 
> Fab, I like the idea of a Usenet group, perhaps even as well as the 
> list if it survives, I find it much easier to follow the threads of 
> ideas, rather than sifting through the current serial stream :)

Can you elaborate on this? I have no problem dealing with the IML as an 
e-mail medium. I have two function key macros which tell Pine, the mail 
reader running on my Internet Service Provider's machine, to move all 
IML messages to their own folder, leaving me with only personal messages 
in my default "Inbox" folder. In addition, Pine sorts all messages by 
subject, even taking into account the "Re: " that often precedes 
responses to a message. This lets me read the IML in thread order.

I have no experience with other mail readers, but must assume that these 
basic functions (separate folders, sort by XXX) are part of any reader 
software.

So, what's the problem, again?


