@toc contents

Subject: RE Premiere
Date:    Tuesday, 19 December 1995 15:37:37 
From:    sherman@netcad.ENET.dec.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

FROM too long. Original FROM is '"Steve NACAD::Sherman LKG2-A/R5 pole AA2 DTN 22
6-6992" <sherman@netcad.ENET.dec.com>'

----------------------  Original Message Follows  ----------------------

I say amen to what Scott wrote (spack@adobe.com).  I'm using Premiere now
and like it.  More, Premiere 4.0 retails for about $425.  But, if you buy
a video display card that includes 4.0 LE, you can upgrade to 4.0 for 
about $150.  I bought a miro DC1 plus card for $400 and am doing the upgrade.
So, for about $550 I'll get Adobe Premiere 4.0 *and* and card that can do
NTSC.  It is *not* broadcast quality, but that's fine by me.  I plan to 
take the JPEG files to a studio to do final taping, bringing along the
edit lists, MIDI files, wave files and so forth.  It's like getting the
miro card for $125.  Some folks have had trouble with this card, but on
my system it's been working fine and the displayed results are acceptable.

I won't go into what card to get.  I chose the miro because it does what
I need for a cheap price.  Anything less would have been unacceptable.  
The next step up would have cost about $700 (a Q-motion) and going to a
PCI-capable board would have cost another $400 or so when considering the
cost of a faster PCI-SCSI2 board.

Steve

