@node IML-691 " MSG-691  Subject: Matrox and Imagine (was: PC Textures) -Reply
@toc contents

Subject: Matrox and Imagine (was: PC Textures) -Reply
Date:    Tuesday, 19 December 1995 17:03:23 
From:    Jon Galley <JGALLEY@rfc.com>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

A Friend of mine is lending me his 4Meg Matrox Millennium until his new
PC arrives (thanks Craig).  I have had NO problems using Imagine 4 in
800X600 mode (with texture previews).  I do not need to run UniVbe
either.

As a side plus,  the realtime textures in TrueSpace are Cool!

jon

>>> Charles Blaquiere <blaq@io.org> 12/19/95 02:01am >>>
> From: Andrew Nunn <apn@moby.demon.co.uk>
>  > Also, has anyone that uses a Matrox Impression Plus card managed
to get
> it to show 24 bit with Imagine?

I don't know about the Imp+, but I (and many others!) have the newer 
Millennium, and its VESA implementation is incompatible with Imagine. If 
you have a 2M WRAM card, Imagine will see 5 VESA modes; if, like me,
you  have the 4M model, Imagine sees no mode at all! The result is that I
can  only work in 640x480x16, and see quickrenders at 320x200x256.
No 24-bit,  no high-res editors, no texture playground, no realtime
greyscale  rendering peeking behind the editor screen!

The good news is that Matrox have been shipped a copy of Imagine, and
 will be checking it out. Keep your fingers crossed, people! In addition, 
the UniVESa folks are busy creating the next version of the popular 
program, which will support the Millennium. (Does the Imp+ use the same 
chipset?) So, there are two solutions in the pipeline.





                       @{"           Thread          682" link IML-682}
                       @{"  -=> RETURN TO CONTENTS!<=-  " link contents}
@endnode


