@node IML-693 " MSG-693  Subject: Re: Outputting a animation to videotape
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Outputting a animation to videotape
Date:    Tuesday, 19 December 1995 17:37:14 
From:    "Ing. Alexander Owen Wallace" <awallace@alpha1.sal.uadec.mx>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

I use to do that before with  the VGA AVER Pro. Normally all my animations
at that time where 649x480 FLICS which I played with ANIPLAY from Autodesk.
The motion was fairly good if you didn't have huge objects close to the
cammera, but if you render 320x200 they move smoothly on a DX2 8mb and
look good on the TV screen (not on vga monitor).

Now I'm useing Movie Machine Pro with the JPEG otion. Though it's not
broadcast quality, It plays back 24 bit full screen avis in real time and
captures video with the same quality. Then let's you output the result to
video. And costs as much as a good ISA vga to tv card.

Any way, if you already have that card, use aniplay, it's public domain
software, if you can't find it I might be able to send it to you as an
attachment after looking for it arround those floppyes

Have a nice day! :)
