Subject: Re: Animation and sound
Date:    Tuesday, 19 December 1995 17:40:32 
From:    "Ing. Alexander Owen Wallace" <awallace@alpha1.sal.uadec.mx>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

Well, you must be useing PC, then, Adobe Premiere is one of the best, it
is used profetionaly. Will generat AVIs the problem is that you micht need
special hardware if want to play them in full screen with interleaved audio.

Animation studio is another (from autodesk) wich is allso a 2d animation
system. I haven't used it, but heard good about it.

Razor pro, is another, etc. Take a look at DV magazine, they review and
advertize plenty of them.

