@node IML-697 " MSG-697  Subject: Imagine Objects.
@toc contents

Subject: Imagine Objects.
Date:    Tuesday, 19 December 1995 19:49:03 
From:    Kevin Alvarado <kra@Rocky.aesthetic.com>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

I created a conversion program that reads Imagine objects and exports them to a
different format.  As of right now, it will convert objects made with v3.0 and
earlier for Amiga created objects.  I don't, as of yet, have v4.0 to work with.
 I'm trying to finetune my conversion program.  If anyone could be so kind, I
need to have a few objects from the different versions of Imaigne.

What I'm looking for:
Amiga v4.0 objects.
PC v3.0 & v4.0 objects.

I could use some primatives, (sphere, plane, torrus, etc) and more complex
objects with a hirarchy.  You don't have to send your life's work or any of
your best objects you don't wish to make public.  I just need a few objects to
test out.

My company is about to release the program and I'd like to make it as robust as
possible before we do.

Thanks,
Kevin -KV- Alvarado

PS, please specify what you send to me so I know that the conversion work
correctly.

-- 
Life is hard and nothing is easily given...
If you want anything out of life you have to fight for it...
Prepare for Kombat!

kra@aesthetic.com
- - - - - - - - -
Kevin Alvarado
(714) 597-4995
Aesthetic Solutions
92 Argonaut, Suite #220
Aliso Viejo, CA  92656

