@node IML-699 " MSG-699  Subject: RE: VRML conversion
@toc contents

Subject: RE: VRML conversion
Date:    Tuesday, 19 December 1995 20:11:17 
From:    bob_landry@corp.Cubic.COM


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


On Tue, 19 Dec 1995 17:19:51 -0500  Craig Andera wrote:
>Has anyone found a tool or set of tools that works well for doing Imagine
>to VRML conversion? Best of all would be something that would take a
>staging file and spit out a VRML file, but I doubt the existence of such a
>beast. I'd settle for being able to convert single objects. 
>
>Any help appreciated. 
>
>-Craig
>
>

Caligari is offering free, the beta version of their VRML browser, FOUNTAIN. It 
can
be downloaded from their Web site at "www.caligari.com". I believe it will direc
tly
read Imagine objects.

- Bob

