@node IML-705 " MSG-705  Subject: Re: Hello, vesa, upgrades
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Hello, vesa, upgrades
Date:    Tuesday, 19 December 1995 22:38:48 
From:    Roger Straub <straub@csn.net>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  



On Tue, 19 Dec 1995, Jeff Fox wrote:

[snip]

> 
> 2. I have seen references to version 3.3 of Imagine. How do I get upgrade
> patchs? What do they cost?

Imagine 3.3 was never available to the public, only to subscribers of the 
Constant Upgrade Program; Impulse sends you 4 updates of Imagine over a 
"one year" period, the last being 4.0. It was a way of getting 4.0, for 
the same price, and getting to play with the new toys while waiting for 
the final release.

Patches don't cost anything, since they don't exist. =) Impulse sent me 4 
upgrades, 3 discs each, and every one had a full copy of Imagine on it. 
Wouldn't it be easier to just release patches? I think this conversation 
came up about a month ago...

> 
> 3. Is there any way to get a real manual for 3.0?
> 

Yeah, contact Impulse and get 4.0! The manual, and all of the extra 
features, really make it worth the cash. =)

> Jeff Fox
> jfox@iadfw.net
> 
> 

