@node IML-712 " MSG-712  Subject: Re: Converting Objects -Reply
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Converting Objects -Reply
Date:    Wednesday, 20 December 1995 00:00:39 
From:    Kevin Alvarado <kra@Rocky.aesthetic.com>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

> Since you indicated that this is a Commercial Product, are
> you offering money or free product for the use of objects to test your
> tool?  Seems only fair - otherwise, I might suggest beta testing your
> software (free obviously) and people will certainly find whatever problems
> exist.

I think my company will release this as freely distributable, shareware or some
other form of public domain, they haven't decided yet.  I am not in a position
to offer money for the use of your objects, that would be up to the President
of the company.  I mentioned earler, that I don't have my version of v4.0 as of
yet.  If my company was to pay for any objects used and roalities, it would be
cheaper to purchases the upgrade from Impulse and I could make my own objects
that I'm looking for.

As far as beta testing, the conversion program is desined for use with Silicon
Graphics workstations.  I worte this conversion program so I could port my
Imagine objects over to the SGI side and use them at work.

I wrote the original message to help make the program as error free as possible
before we release it.  If you'd like a copy of it, I'll send you one once we
release it to the public.

Kevin -KV- Alvarado.

-- 
