@node IML-714 " MSG-714  Subject: Re: Converting Objects
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Converting Objects
Date:    Wednesday, 20 December 1995 00:20:39 
From:    Kevin Alvarado <kra@Rocky.aesthetic.com>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

> I think you might be underestimating how complex an imagine object might be.
> Then again, perhaps you are not, I do not know.

> Are you taking into account:
>     States
>     Bones
>     Textures
>     Maps
>     Effects
>
> If not, your converter might be rather limited.

I read the document that was relased by Impulse written by S. Kirvan that
explained the object format of Imagine (im3texdoc.lha ).  I know about all the
stuff that's in v3.0 Imagine objects.  That's why I'm asking for v4.0
primatives and other objects.  I would like to make the program as error free
before its release.

The program will read the object files created from the detail editor and only
use the points and faces data to create the object for use with a Silicon
Graphics workstation.  All face atributes (color, transparency, specular
values, etc) per face are used.  Anything else is ignored.  Maps, are just a
file reference to were Imagine can find the image on disk.  The actual map is
not in the file, same with textures.

