@node IML-735 " MSG-735  Subject: Re: Lightsource morphing?
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Lightsource morphing?
Date:    Wednesday, 20 December 1995 11:49:46 
From:    "Frank.VanDerAuwera" <fvdauwer@uia.ua.ac.be>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

I am not quite shure about this, and I can't check right now, cause I'm 
at work, but i seem to remember that the "diafragm and exposure time" 
equivalent of imagine is by default automatic. What I mean to say is: if 
your torpedo is the only light source, and it changes intensity, then 
probably imagine adjusts its "camera light sensitivity" in each frame to 
the new average light level, resulting in your light source appearing 
m.o.l. the same in every frame. There must be a way of setting camera 
sensitivity (or "exposure" if you wish) by hand, but i don't remember how 
for the moment. Maybe one of the camera's axis sizes?


Frank Van der Auwera
University of Antwerp library

fvdauwer@uia.ac.be
fauwera@lib.ua.ac.be


