@node IML-742 " MSG-742  Subject: Re: Lightsource morphing?
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Lightsource morphing?
Date:    Wednesday, 20 December 1995 17:27:25 
From:    RobSampson@aol.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

In a message dated 95-12-20 01:31:17 EST, you write:

>Is there any way to get a lightsource to morph properly? I'm creating a 
>photon torpedo impact on an energy shield (I know it's cliche, but it's 
>fun!). I want the light from the first frame of the impact to fade away 
>to nothing in about 10 frames, but it doesn't seem to be working! The 
>lightsource fades slightly in the first 9 frames, then disappears 
>completely in the 10th frame! Thanks! =)

Well since your only talking about 10 frames, you can fine tune your control
by creating the lights you want at the intensity in each frame that you want
and then just copy the position strip for each.  Not practicle for 20 or more
frames, but for what you are doing it may give you exactly the control you
want.

Bob.............
Imagine renderings.
http://home.aol.com/robsampson





