@node IML-744 " MSG-744  Subject: Re: Clothes on Humanoid?
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Clothes on Humanoid?
Date:    Wednesday, 20 December 1995 17:27:26 
From:    RobSampson@aol.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

In a message dated 95-12-20 02:54:44 EST, you write:

>Many thanks- The specific problem is to put a leotard type costume on the
>female figure...

Ah, ok the it becomes quite a bit easier.  In fact you may be able to use a
procedural texutre and then just define subgroups on the object to restrain
the texture to where you want the clothing.  If you are doing just stills,
then I would suggest posing the figure as required and merging the body into
one.  It would make the definition of a subgroup for a textured approach to
clothing much easier.  It is the approach I used after modifying a humanoid
into satan.  However in that case I was texuring the entire body skin wise
and so did not require a subgroup.  If however you are bringing the entire
thing over into Alias, then you are on your own:)))  That stuff is way beyond
the reach of amatuer like me:)

Bob.............
