Subject: Re: Imagine Objects.
Date:    Wednesday, 20 December 1995 20:51:49 
From:    Kevin Alvarado <kra@Rocky.aesthetic.com>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

> Well, since PC and Amiga formats are the same (Imagine is a direct port
> to the PC side, so writes the same file structure), this is easy. I'll
> send you a coupla objects made in Amiga 4.0. Then you'll have all the
> bases covered.
>
> Just out of old-fashioned curiosity, what format does this program output?

I've heard that the PC and Amiga Imagine objects have a suttle difference, that
fact that the PC's hardware likes its data in Least Significant Bit order
verses the Amiga's Most Significant Bit order.  I'm trying to find out if I
need to have a seprate PC version of the conversion program.

I appreciate and gladly accept your offer of 4.0 objects.  Thanaks.

Right now, I can't let out what format the objects are converted to.  The
company I work for is small and has limited resources.  If any of the bigger
companies found out what we do here the could put more resources into
development and produce a similar product before we even finish or development.
 The conversion program is a tool I wrote to help us with what we do here.
 It's not ment to be our big product.  When my boss gives the ok, I'll post
what format it exports to.  I can say that it exports to SGI workstations.

Thanks again,
