@node IML-749 " MSG-749  Subject: Re: Converting Objects -Reply
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Converting Objects -Reply
Date:    Wednesday, 20 December 1995 21:05:53 
From:    Kevin Alvarado <kra@Rocky.aesthetic.com>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

> I occasionally convert Imagine objects into Wavefront .obj objects and
> import them into Alias. Generally they're OK, but I always have to flip all
> the faces the same direction using a new feature in v.6 of Alias.

I've ran in to this problem as well.  I think it's because Imagine's renderer
doesn't care which why the polygon's normals face (Inside or outside of the
object).  The format we use it defently matters which way the normals face.  I
had to address that very problem.  To a degree I've found a solution to this.
 It will all depend on how you create the object.  I use the object's axis as a
reference point as to what the inside of the object is.  The object's polygons
will always face away from the objects axis.  The limitation with this approach
is that if the object's axis is outside of the object, half of the object will
face the inside (awayfrom the axis) and the other half will face the outside
(again, away from the axis).

David, I think you'll like my little utility I worte.  I'll keep you posted.
-KV-

