@node IML-751 " MSG-751  Subject: Re: Hail and Farewell (fwd)
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Hail and Farewell (fwd)
Date:    Wednesday, 20 December 1995 22:42:15 
From:    Ted Stethem <tstethem@linknet.kitsap.lib.wa.us>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

  If Perry can set up an ftp site, it would be a very good thing, IMNSHO. 
Yes, aminet is there but PC-types don't feel all that comfortable sending 
things up there plus it is an unwritten policy that the quality of 
uploads to Aminet maintain certain standards, usually of a finished 
nature. 
  What would be nice about a more general Imagine ftp site would be that 
you could have a specific area for uploading and downloading just test 
anims or images, things that aren't necessarily completed. For example, 
say the area was named Imagine/pix/help. You could send an image there 
that just looked awful because you couldn't get a brushmap placed right 
on an irregular object, then you could get on the IML, say you have 
uploaded Junk.image, please HEELLLPPPP!, then people could look at it and 
provide their helpful suggestions. 
  Plus, you could have two directories, say ImaginePC and ImagineAmy, 
then those things that were specific to the machine could be in those 
areas like custom textures, texture source code, whatever.
  And, finally, a really big service it would provide is eliminating the 
need to UUENCODE files to the list.
  The one big difficulty with this idea is the need for some kind of file 
management, primarily to check for viruses. I don't know how the Aminet 
does this but I have the understanding that files are screened for 
viruses somehow.

On Wed, 20 Dec 1995, Duncan wrote:

