@node IML-753 " MSG-753  Subject: Strange cropping in animation
@toc contents

Subject: Strange cropping in animation
Date:    Wednesday, 20 December 1995 23:30:55 
From:    Jeff Fox <jfox@iadfw.net>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

I am using Imagine 3.0 on a peecee. I have 16 meg of RAM.
I have created a 60 frame animation (my first!) of an object rotating around
it's Y axis. I am using the rotate2 effect to do this.  There is only one
object, no groups, children, etc.  The object is a light source. There is
one light source in the scene. The light is a point light with no shadows.
It is not a cone or cylindrical light source. (I played with those and know
that parts of an object won't be lit).
Frames 1-53 look fine, so does frame 60. Frames 54-59 are cropped on the
left and right sides. Only the middle of the object renders.
This only happens in trace mode. Scanline and lower render the whole object.
I am rendering to 320x200x24bit .tga; I tried 80x80x24bit and got the same
results.
Any ideas?

Jeff Fox
jfox@iadfw.net
http://lmg.com/upstage/bios/jeff.htm


