@node IML-754 " MSG-754  Subject: 3DS-IOB
@toc contents

Subject: 3DS-IOB
Date:    Wednesday, 20 December 1995 23:38:53 
From:    Charles Blaquiere <blaq@io.org>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

> From: ISRAEL@procergs.com.br
> 
> The problem is that the model comes with hard edges in ALL edges, and
> nothing is able to fix it, even using the "make soft edges" tool.

If all edges look sharp, even when you explicitely make them soft, then 
maybe they're not the same edge. Perhaps the converted object has a 
_separate_ set of 3 points for every face, which means that every edge 
is unconnected to the neighbouring face. I would suggest using Merge to 
see if the point count, as seen in the Find requester, decreases. If 
that's the case, then you may try setting sharp and soft edges again.


                       @{"           Thread          750" link IML-750}
                       @{"  -=> RETURN TO CONTENTS!<=-  " link contents}
@endnode


