@node IML-756 " MSG-756  Subject: Lightsource morphing?
@toc contents

Subject: Lightsource morphing?
Date:    Wednesday, 20 December 1995 23:51:36 
From:    Charles Blaquiere <blaq@io.org>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

> From: Roger Straub <straub@csn.net>
> 
> The lightsource fades slightly in the first 9 frames, then disappears
> completely in the 10th frame! Thanks! =)

I assume you're morphing the _intensity_ of the light, and not the 
"Light" attribute itself, which is an on/off flag?

If you're morphing intensity, then maybe you have a weird spline morph
curve. Try turning off the "use spline interpolation" button. For
example, a curve with #0 value = 0 and #1 value = 999 would produce a
sharp change towards the end of the morph. 


                       @{"           Thread          735" link IML-735}
                       @{"  -=> RETURN TO CONTENTS!<=-  " link contents}
@endnode


