@node IML-762 " MSG-762  Subject: Bone Question/Problem
@toc contents

Subject: Bone Question/Problem
Date:    Thursday, 21 December 1995 08:46:30 
From:    jbk4@psu.edu (Prophet)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

Question first.  When constructing bones objects and states, should the
SHAPE data be saved for each state or only the default state?

I have been saving SHAPE data for each state but I noticed this problem.

Use the boned hand included with IMagine.  Create an open state that
retains shape data.  Then bend a finger.  Create another state, bend,
that also retains the shape data.

If you create a state anim, morphing between the open & bend states,
the finger will shrink as it is tweening between the states.  If you
were to use the TWEEN function to go from open to bend, you would
see a clearly deformed finger(shrunken).  Imagine isn't correctly
updating the bones during tween stages.  If I take the shrunken tweened
hand and then do a BONES UPDATE myself, the finger will be corrected.

This is all occuring when I've saved the SHAPE data with each state
created.

If I only save SHAPE data for the default state then the problem
doesn't arise.  Imagine will correctly update the bone structure.

So when am I supposed to save SHAPE data, other than the DEFAULT state?
What about the other state datas(face colour, properties, texture/brush)?
I always retain GROUPING.


Jaeson K.
