@node IML-763 " MSG-763  Subject: Re: Imagine Objects.
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Imagine Objects.
Date:    Thursday, 21 December 1995 09:26:55 
From:    Martin Caspersson <SA9418@ida.utb.hb.se>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

> 
> I've heard that the PC and Amiga Imagine objects have a suttle difference, tha
t
> fact that the PC's hardware likes its data in Least Significant Bit order
> verses the Amiga's Most Significant Bit order.  I'm trying to find out if I
> need to have a seprate PC version of the conversion program.

I've heard that since Imagine was originally for the Amiga only, the 
objects are stored in Most Significant Bit order. When the PC 
version loads in objects it reverses the bit order. In my experience 
no converter is needed.

