@node IML-775 " MSG-775  Subject: V3.0 Broken Stuff
@toc contents

Subject: V3.0 Broken Stuff
Date:    Sunday, 24 December 1995 00:56:48 
From:    Ted Stethem <tstethem@linknet.kitsap.lib.wa.us>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

  I see another round of "I'm trying to xxxxx in V3.0 and can't seem to 
.....".
  The things that DON'T WORK RIGHT IN VERSION 3.0:

1. DXF Loader - very few .DXF files will load in
2. POSTSCRIPT Loader - it doesn't work very well either, only specific 
Type 1.
3. Starfield - animating (moving) starfield won't; it was broken in V 3.0.
4. Smart Bones - not so smart, the menu items for Big and Small are reversed.
5. Global Brushmap Reflection - don't work, got broken, was fixed with a 
patch.

  There were a bunch of other bugs and I think somebody put up the 
complete list of bugs to the list several months ago. Check out the 
archives if you are interested.
  So, for everybody that got it free, its because it is full of bugs but 
that is not to say it is unusable. You should know, you get what you 
pay for, and sometimes, NOT.
  A lot of bugs were fixed in V3.1 and V4.0 ended up with the bugfixes 
plus a lot of really neat extra features. It is worth it to upgrade.
  

                       @{"           Thread          797" link IML-797}
                       @{"  -=> RETURN TO CONTENTS!<=-  " link contents}
@endnode


@node IML-776 " MSG-776  Subject: PAR under Cyberstorm 060 + WHY IML?
