Subject: PAR under Cyberstorm 060 + WHY IML?
Date:    Monday, 25 December 1995 01:31:55 
From:    woldh@mother.norconnect.no (Per Sverre Wold-Hansen)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


I've tried to run my PAR v2.30 (PAL) on my Cyberstorm 060
accellerated A4000 but am having problems: Crash.

I therefore have to run it on my A3000. I do my Imagine renderings
on A4000 and transfer to A3000, but want to run PAR on A4000.
That would both save me the time of transfer and give faster
packing to the PAR.

Any suggestions for a fix?

Also:

I've just joined the NET, and also the Imagine Mailing List service.

Being a newbee(?) in this field I keep wondering: WHY the IML?

I'm in no way trying to downplay all the work put into
this service (and I love getting mail...), but why the
effort?

To me it seems that a regular newsgroup on the Net would
do close to the same thing - Or not?

Obviously the collection of all the IML-mail into "packages" is
a very neat and helpful thing. I have benefitted from those
collections myself before joining the Internet - Getting
them from a local BBS. But couldn't the same thing be achieved
with a regular newsgroup?

Just wondering...



