On Tue, 26 Dec 1995, William Bogan wrote:

> Hi folks,
> I've got a friend who has a Pentium w/PCI video board. The splash screen 
> for 4.0 is garbled and the quickrender is also and if he does a 'show' in 
> the project editor that too is garbled. However, the splash screen from 2.0 
> works beautifully. He would like to know what the difference is between them.
> Or, why one works fine (2.0) the other (4.0) not?


    It sounds like he needs a VESA driver. Look for a program called 
UniVBE. I don't know much about it, except that it is shareware, and will 
fix problems with video cards that do not have VESA compatability 
built-in. Sorry I can't give an ftp site or more info about it, but I 
don't use it. I just know it exists :) Good luck!

                              SJG

Imagine 3.0/P5-100/16megs/beginner---

