@node IML-782 " MSG-782  Subject: Re: BUG
@toc contents

Subject: Re: BUG
Date:    Tuesday, 26 December 1995 18:19:49 
From:    Kevin Alvarado <kra@Rocky.aesthetic.com>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

> How come that the values in a texture changes slightly each time
> you save and load an object. You know setting bevel filter to -1
> changes to -0.999985. Is this a bug?

It sounds like you're using an integer version of Imagine.  I use the floating
point version mostly.  Reciently, my accelerator card went bad and I had to
send it to the magnafacture for repairs.  So I'm forced to use the integer
version.  I've noticed that MOST if not all negative values are changed to
something similar ( -2.0 = -1.9999985 ).  I think it's the algorithim that
Imagine is using to convert integer values to floating point values.  Something
get's lost in the translation.

-KV-

