@node IML-783 " MSG-783  Subject: Imagine Object Conversion Program
@toc contents

Subject: Imagine Object Conversion Program
Date:    Tuesday, 26 December 1995 19:34:50 
From:    Kevin Alvarado <kra@Rocky.aesthetic.com>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

OK, my conversion program is now officialy relised and freely distributable.

I have created a conversion program that will convert Imagine Detail editor
polygonal objects into a format that can be used on a Silicon Graphics
workstation.  The format it converts to is OpenInventor.  I call it "imtoiv".

It converts all of Imagine's face set objects from versions v1.0 to v4.0
objects.  It doesn't however, convert blob objects completely, it can only
convert blob objects into CGS sphere objects that create the blob.  Blobmeshes
should convert without problems.

I have three working exicutable versions of the program.  One for the SGI the
other for Amiga and the thrid for PCs.  I'm createing an archive of all three
and a ReadMe.txt file to go with the archive.  I will upload it to various
places, Aminet and GEnie are a two places that come to mind.  I don't have a
CompuServ or an AOL account, but if I can find someone who can upload it there
for me I'll do that.

It's great to see your objects move around and shaded in real-time on and SGI!
 This program is for anyone who uses Imagine and uses a SGI workstation.

Anyone on the Imagine Mailing List who is intrested let me know and I'll send
you a copy.

-KV-

