@node IML-786 " MSG-786  Subject: Re: Strange cropping in animation
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Strange cropping in animation
Date:    Wednesday, 27 December 1995 23:50:39 
From:    DaminMK@aol.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

Jeff:

     I had a simular problem with my renderings a while back.  It was that
the world size was incorrect.  The result was any object (or any part of any
object) that was outside the area defined by the world size didn't appear in
the rendered scene.  To fix this: go into the Stage Editor and determine the
overall size of the scene (using the Grid Size function to create a visual
bounding box around the objects).  Note the size and go into the Action
Editor.  With the editor set to Info mode click on the Size bar in Globals
and enter the X, Y, and Z values for the world size.
     Also, the manual states that Imagine will automatically set the
appropriate world size if the Size bar is set to 0, 0, 0.  However I've tried
this and it doesn't always work, especially if you have lightsources a great
distance away for the rest of the scene.
Hope this info helps to fix your ploblem.

                       @{"           Thread          477" link IML-477}
                       @{"  -=> RETURN TO CONTENTS!<=-  " link contents}
@endnode


@node IML-787 " MSG-787  Subject: Smoothing tool
@toc contents

Subject: Smoothing tool
Date:    Thursday, 28 December 1995 05:04:26 
From:    Gabriele.Scibilia@p24.f211.n332.z2.fidonet.org


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

FROM too long. Original FROM is 'Gabriele.Scibilia@p24.f211.n332.z2.fidonet.org 
(Gabriele Scibilia)'

----------------------  Original Message Follows  ----------------------


Happy rendering Imagineers,


Receiver, a Smoothing tool example, By Gabriele Scibilia.

        This uses Imagine v4.0 Smoothing tool feature, it is based
upon a Lightwave Metaform tutorial by James Trew; here it is how use
new Smoothing tool to make a receiver.

        In the Detail Editor:

    - Add axis at 0, 0, 0.
    - Pick select, Lock to grid (grid size is 20 units), Add lines.
    - Click left mouse button to the following coordinates:
        0, 0, -40; -20, 0, -40; -60, 0, -20; -80, 0, -40;
        -100, 0, -40; -100, 0, 0; -60, 0, 60; 0, 0, 60.
    - Enter Mold requestor, Sweep: sweep angle 360, 8 sections.
    - Copy and Paste object.
    - Transformation, position the new object to 460, 0, 0.
    - Transformation, align the new object to 12, 0, 90.
    - Pick the original object and align to -12, 0, 90.

        Now we model the handle:

    - Add axis at 200, -25, 50.
    - Pick select, Lock to grid, Add lines to:
        80, -25, 0; 40, -25, 60; 180, -25, 80; 300, -25, 80;
        420, -25, 60; 380, -25, 0; 280, -25, 20; 200, -25, 20;
        80, -25, 0.
    - Enter Pick edges method.
    - Pick the upper 3 edges (multipick), Set edge line.
    - Pick the remaining edges, Fill to edge line.
    - Pick object method.
    - Extrude the shape 50 units.
    - Pick all faces, Fracture.
    - Pick object, multipick all objects, Slice.
    - Delete the intersecting resulting objects.
    - Join and Merge all objs.
    - Pick all faces, Fracture, Smoothing tool, smoothing factor to 10.



I had a dream, When I was young,
A dream of sweet illusion,
A glimpse of hope and unity,
And visions of one sweet union,
But a cold wind blows,
And a dark rain falls,
And in my heart it shows,
Look what they've done to my dream.

"minix5@disi.unige.it"
"G.Scibilia@agora.stm.it"
"Imagine Mailing List, IML FAQer"

