@node IML-794 " MSG-794  Subject: Contest - January
@toc contents

Subject: Contest - January
Date:    Friday, 29 December 1995 16:45:09 
From:    vview@cswnet.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

THEME:

 - - Christmas  - -

This should be fresh in everyones' minds. This can be anything from 
Santa and his sleigh, presents under the tree, shopping at the mall, a pile of b
ills on the desk, as long as it has something to do
 with christmas.

DEADLINE:

Uploads will be taken from 1/14/96 through midnight 1/20/95. Any 
uploads received after the deadline will be deleted. To submit an contest entry 
an entry form must be requested from vview@cswnet.com.

Include the words entry form in your subject line. The entry form 
should include a short description of the image (in case of filename mixup), Ima
gine version # used, and platform used. Further entry
 instructions will be forwarded with your filename to be used for 
upload. Anonymous filenames will be used for judging fairness and for easier fil
e handling. (ftp upload directory has to be worked ou
t yet)

JUDGING:

Voting will take place the following week. An ftp site will be 
announced for members to download the entries for voting. More will follow on voting. All top placing entries should post to the list sh
ort description of how the image was created. This could include 
textures used, modeling techniques, design techniques, and other tip and tricks.


GENERAL RULES:

+ This contest is open to members of the Imagine Mailing List.

+ All work is to be done with Imagine. The only exceptions are images 
used for brushmaps. No third party products. No post-processing other the format
 conversion. All work including objects should be
 original.

+ One entry per person. Once the files are uploaded they will not be 
able to be retrieved or updated, so make them right the first time.

+ All entries will be in .jpg format with a size no larger then 50k.

+ Emphasis should be on both design and techniques.

+ All entrants will not worry about who wins or about who is the 
better artist. The newest user might have a design technique that would benefit 
everyone on the list. Everyone is encouraged to partic
ipate. This is meant to be a learning experience and fun time.

+ All entrants will enjoy participating, otherwise this contest 
failed.

+ All ties will be just that, a tie.

+ Do not post entries or applications to the list. E-mail them direct 
to me as indicated above. 

Rick
Imagine 4 - Pentium 60 - 8 meg - middle+

                       @{"           Thread          706" link IML-706}
                       @{"  -=> RETURN TO CONTENTS!<=-  " link contents}
@endnode


