@node IML-796 " MSG-796  Subject: Re: Usenet IML anyone??
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Usenet IML anyone??
Date:    Saturday, 30 December 1995 12:21:09 
From:    Andrew Nunn <apn_iml@moby.demon.co.uk>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


>I'm quite willing to investigate the setting up of a Usenet group to
>replace the beloved IML, similar to that enjoyed by Lightwave and 3D
>Studio.

I posted the above a couple of weeks ago. The votes flooded in like a
British Euro-Election (ie they didn't). In all there were 5 in favour and
3 against.

Things have moved on a little with Perrys' new listserver arrangements
meaning that the traditional list lives on. The real benefit that Usenet
would have is that articles could be selected for download by topic.

To set up a Usenet group would take about two months, and would still be
subject to a vote at the end. There would of course be those who would vote
against just because they prefer some other package, so without a large
enough support to begin with, it hardly seems worth the effort. The plans
are therefore on hold at present.

Andrew Nunn
apn@moby.demon.co.uk


                       @{"           Thread          775" link IML-775}
